lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_addsub12t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) ) = 
  ( B \<ca> ( A \<cs> C ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<ca> B ) = ( B \<ca> A )" 
     by (rule MMI_axaddcom)
   from S1 have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> C ) = 
     ( ( B \<ca> A ) \<cs> C )" by (rule MMI_opreq1d)
   from S2 have S3: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> C ) = ( ( B \<ca> A ) \<cs> C )" 
     by (rule MMI_3adant3)
   have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> C ) = 
     ( A \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) )" by (rule MMI_addsubasst)
   have S5: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( B \<ca> A ) \<cs> C ) = 
     ( B \<ca> ( A \<cs> C ) )" by (rule MMI_addsubasst)
   from S5 have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( B \<ca> A ) \<cs> C ) = ( B \<ca> ( A \<cs> C ) )" by (rule MMI_3com12)
   from S3 S4 S6 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( A \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) ) = ( B \<ca> ( A \<cs> C ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_3eqtr3d)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_addsubass: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> C ) = ( A \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A3 have S3: "C ∈ ℂ".
   have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> C ) = 
     ( A \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) )" by (rule MMI_addsubasst)
   from S1 S2 S3 S4 show "( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> C ) = 
     ( A \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) )" by (rule MMI_mp3an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_addsub: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> C ) = ( ( A \<cs> C ) \<ca> B )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A3 have S3: "C ∈ ℂ".
   have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> C ) = 
     ( ( A \<cs> C ) \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_addsubt)
   from S1 S2 S3 S4 show "( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> C ) = 
     ( ( A \<cs> C ) \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_mp3an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_2addsubt: 
   shows "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
  ( ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<ca> C ) \<cs> D ) = ( ( ( A \<ca> C ) \<cs> D ) \<ca> B )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<ca> C ) = 
     ( ( A \<ca> C ) \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_add23t)
   from S1 have S2: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<ca> C ) = ( ( A \<ca> C ) \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_3expa)
   from S2 have S3: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<ca> C ) = ( ( A \<ca> C ) \<ca> B )" 
     by (rule MMI_adantrr)
   from S3 have S4: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<ca> C ) \<cs> D ) = 
     ( ( ( A \<ca> C ) \<ca> B ) \<cs> D )" by (rule MMI_opreq1d)
   have S5: "( ( A \<ca> C ) ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A \<ca> C ) \<ca> B ) \<cs> D ) = 
     ( ( ( A \<ca> C ) \<cs> D ) \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_addsubt)
   from S5 have S6: "( ( A \<ca> C ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( B ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A \<ca> C ) \<ca> B ) \<cs> D ) = 
     ( ( ( A \<ca> C ) \<cs> D ) \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_3expb)
   have S7: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<ca> C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axaddcl)
   from S6 S7 have S8: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( B ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A \<ca> C ) \<ca> B ) \<cs> D ) = 
     ( ( ( A \<ca> C ) \<cs> D ) \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_sylan)
   from S8 have S9: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A \<ca> C ) \<ca> B ) \<cs> D ) = 
     ( ( ( A \<ca> C ) \<cs> D ) \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_an4s)
   from S4 S9 show "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<ca> C ) \<cs> D ) = 
     ( ( ( A \<ca> C ) \<cs> D ) \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_eqtrd)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_negneg: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) = A"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S1 have S2: "( (\<cn>  A) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_negcl)
   from S2 have S3: "( ( (\<cn>  A) ) \<ca> ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) ) = 𝟬" 
     by (rule MMI_negid)
   from S3 have S4: "( A \<ca> ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) \<ca> ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) ) ) = 
     ( A \<ca> 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_opreq2i)
   from A1 have S5: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S5 have S6: "( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_negid)
   from S6 have S7: "( ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) \<ca> ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) ) = 
     ( 𝟬 \<ca> ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq1i)
   from A1 have S8: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S2 have S9: "( (\<cn>  A) ) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S2 have S10: "( (\<cn>  A) ) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S10 have S11: "( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_negcl)
   from S8 S9 S11 have S12: 
     "( ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) \<ca> ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) ) = 
     ( A \<ca> ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) \<ca> ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_addass)
   from S11 have S13: "( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S13 have S14: "( 𝟬 \<ca> ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) ) = 
     ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) )" by (rule MMI_addid2)
   from S7 S12 S14 have S15: 
     "( A \<ca> ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) \<ca> ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) ) ) = 
     ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) )" by (rule MMI_3eqtr3)
   from A1 have S16: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S16 have S17: "( A \<ca> 𝟬 ) = A" by (rule MMI_addid1)
   from S4 S15 S17 show "( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) = A" by (rule MMI_3eqtr3)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_subid: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( A \<cs> A ) = 𝟬"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A1 have S2: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) = ( A \<cs> A )" 
     by (rule MMI_negsub)
   from A1 have S4: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S4 have S5: "( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_negid)
   from S3 S5 show "( A \<cs> A ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_eqtr3)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_subid1: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( A \<cs> 𝟬 ) = A"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S1 have S2: "( 𝟬 \<ca> A ) = A" by (rule MMI_addid2)
   from A1 have S3: "A ∈ ℂ".
   have S4: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from A1 have S5: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S3 S4 S5 have S6: "( A \<cs> 𝟬 ) = A ⟷ ( 𝟬 \<ca> A ) = A" 
     by (rule MMI_subadd)
   from S2 S6 show "( A \<cs> 𝟬 ) = A" by (rule MMI_mpbir)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_negnegt: 
   shows "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) = A"
proof -
   have S1: "A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ ( (\<cn>  A) ) = 
     ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_negeq)
   from S1 have S2: "A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) = 
     ( \<cn> ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_negeqd)
   have S3: "A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 )" 
     by (rule MMI_id)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
     ( ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) = A ⟷ 
     ( \<cn> ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ) = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_eqeq12d)
   have S5: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S5 have S6: "if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   from S6 have S7: "( \<cn> ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ) = 
     if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_negneg)
   from S4 S7 show "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) = A" by (rule MMI_dedth)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_subnegt: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<cs> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = ( A \<ca> B )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) = ( A \<cs> ( (\<cn>  B) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_negsubt)
   have S2: "B ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_negclt)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) = ( A \<cs> ( (\<cn>  B) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_sylan2)
   have S4: "B ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = B" by (rule MMI_negnegt)
   from S4 have S5: "B ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) = 
     ( A \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_opreq2d)
   from S5 have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) = ( A \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S3 S6 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<cs> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
     ( A \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_eqtr3d)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_subidt: 
   shows "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( A \<cs> A ) = 𝟬"
proof -
   have S1: "( A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ∧ A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⟶ 
     ( A \<cs> A ) = ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cs> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_opreq12)
   from S1 have S2: "A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
     ( A \<cs> A ) = ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cs> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_anidms)
   from S2 have S3: "A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<cs> A ) = 𝟬 ⟷ 
     ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cs> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) = 𝟬 )" 
     by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   have S4: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S4 have S5: "if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   from S5 have S6: 
     "( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cs> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) = 𝟬" 
     by (rule MMI_subid)
   from S3 S6 show "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( A \<cs> A ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_dedth)
qed

(************** 64-73 *************************************)
lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_subid1t: 
   shows "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( A \<cs> 𝟬 ) = A"
proof -
   have S1: "A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ ( A \<cs> 𝟬 ) = 
     ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cs> 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   have S2: "A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
     A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_id)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<cs> 𝟬 ) = A ⟷ ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cs> 𝟬 ) = 
     if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq12d)
   have S4: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S4 have S5: "if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   from S5 have S6: "( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cs> 𝟬 ) = 
     if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_subid1)
   from S3 S6 show "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( A \<cs> 𝟬 ) = A" by (rule MMI_dedth)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_pncant: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> B ) = A"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> B ) = 
     ( A \<ca> ( B \<cs> B ) )" by (rule MMI_addsubasst)
   from S1 have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ ( B ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> B ) = ( A \<ca> ( B \<cs> B ) )" by (rule MMI_3expb)
   from S2 have S3: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> B ) = 
     ( A \<ca> ( B \<cs> B ) )" by (rule MMI_anabsan2)
   have S4: "B ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( B \<cs> B ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_subidt)
   from S4 have S5: "B ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( A \<ca> ( B \<cs> B ) ) = ( A \<ca> 𝟬 )" 
     by (rule MMI_opreq2d)
   have S6: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( A \<ca> 𝟬 ) = A" by (rule MMI_ax0id)
   from S5 S6 have S7: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<ca> ( B \<cs> B ) ) = A" 
     by (rule MMI_sylan9eqr)
   from S3 S7 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> B ) = A" 
     by (rule MMI_eqtrd)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_pncan2t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> A ) = B"
proof -
   have S1: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( B \<ca> A ) = ( A \<ca> B )" 
     by (rule MMI_axaddcom)
   from S1 have S2: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( B \<ca> A ) \<cs> A ) = 
     ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> A )" by (rule MMI_opreq1d)
   have S3: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( B \<ca> A ) \<cs> A ) = B" 
     by (rule MMI_pncant)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> A ) = B" by (rule MMI_eqtr3d)
   from S4 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> A ) = B" 
     by (rule MMI_ancoms)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_npcant: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> B ) = A"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> B ) = ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> B )" 
     by (rule MMI_addsubt)
   from S1 have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ ( B ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> B ) = ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_3expb)
   from S2 have S3: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> B ) = ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> B )" 
     by (rule MMI_anabsan2)
   have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> B ) = A" 
     by (rule MMI_pncant)
   from S3 S4 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> B ) = A" 
     by (rule MMI_eqtr3d)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_npncant: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
  ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) ) = ( A \<cs> C )"
proof -
   have S1: "( ( A \<cs> B ) ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> B ) \<cs> C ) = 
     ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) )" by (rule MMI_addsubasst)
   have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<cs> B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_subclt)
   from S2 have S3: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( A \<cs> B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3adant3)
   have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3simp2)
   have S5: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ C ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3simp3)
   from S1 S3 S4 S5 have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> B ) \<cs> C ) = 
     ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) )" by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   have S7: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> B ) = A" 
     by (rule MMI_npcant)
   from S7 have S8: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> B ) \<cs> C ) = ( A \<cs> C )" 
     by (rule MMI_opreq1d)
   from S8 have S9: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> B ) \<cs> C ) = ( A \<cs> C )" 
     by (rule MMI_3adant3)
   from S6 S9 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) ) = ( A \<cs> C )" 
     by (rule MMI_eqtr3d)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_nppcant: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
  ( ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> C ) \<ca> B ) = ( A \<ca> C )"
proof -
   have S1: "( ( A \<cs> B ) ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> C ) \<ca> B ) = 
     ( ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> B ) \<ca> C )" by (rule MMI_add23t)
   have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<cs> B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_subclt)
   from S2 have S3: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<cs> B ) ∈ ℂ" 
     by (rule MMI_3adant3)
   have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ C ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3simp3)
   have S5: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3simp2)
   from S1 S3 S4 S5 have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> C ) \<ca> B ) = 
     ( ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> B ) \<ca> C )" by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   have S7: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> B ) = A" 
     by (rule MMI_npcant)
   from S7 have S8: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> B ) \<ca> C ) = ( A \<ca> C )" 
     by (rule MMI_opreq1d)
   from S8 have S9: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> B ) \<ca> C ) = ( A \<ca> C )" 
     by (rule MMI_3adant3)
   from S6 S9 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> C ) \<ca> B ) = ( A \<ca> C )" by (rule MMI_eqtrd)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_subneg: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( A \<cs> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = ( A \<ca> B )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   have S3: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<cs> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = ( A \<ca> B )" 
     by (rule MMI_subnegt)
   from S1 S2 S3 show "( A \<cs> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = ( A \<ca> B )" 
     by (rule MMI_mp2an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_subeq0: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( A \<cs> B ) = 𝟬 ⟷ A = B"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = ( A \<cs> B )" 
     by (rule MMI_negsub)
   from S3 have S4: "( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 𝟬 ⟷ ( A \<cs> B ) = 𝟬" 
     by (rule MMI_eqeq1i)
   have S5: "( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 𝟬 ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) \<ca> B ) = ( 𝟬 \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   from S4 S5 have S6: "( A \<cs> B ) = 𝟬 ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) \<ca> B ) = ( 𝟬 \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_sylbir)
   from A1 have S7: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S8: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S8 have S9: "( (\<cn>  B) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_negcl)
   from A2 have S10: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S7 S9 S10 have S11: "( ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) \<ca> B ) = 
     ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) )" by (rule MMI_add23)
   from A1 have S12: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S13: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S9 have S14: "( (\<cn>  B) ) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S12 S13 S14 have S15: "( ( A \<ca> B ) \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
     ( A \<ca> ( B \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) )" by (rule MMI_addass)
   from A2 have S16: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S16 have S17: "( B \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_negid)
   from S17 have S18: "( A \<ca> ( B \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) = ( A \<ca> 𝟬 )" 
     by (rule MMI_opreq2i)
   from A1 have S19: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S19 have S20: "( A \<ca> 𝟬 ) = A" by (rule MMI_addid1)
   from S18 S20 have S21: "( A \<ca> ( B \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) = A" 
     by (rule MMI_eqtr)
   from S11 S15 S21 have S22: "( ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) \<ca> B ) = A" 
     by (rule MMI_3eqtr)
   from A2 have S23: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S23 have S24: "( 𝟬 \<ca> B ) = B" by (rule MMI_addid2)
   from S6 S22 S24 have S25: "( A \<cs> B ) = 𝟬 ⟶ A = B" 
     by (rule MMI_3eqtr3g)
   have S26: "A = B ⟶ ( A \<cs> B ) = ( B \<cs> B )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   from A2 have S27: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S27 have S28: "( B \<cs> B ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_subid)
   from S26 S28 have S29: "A = B ⟶ ( A \<cs> B ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_syl6eq)
   from S25 S29 show "( A \<cs> B ) = 𝟬 ⟷ A = B" by (rule MMI_impbi)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_neg11: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( (\<cn>  A) ) = ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ A = B"
proof -
   have S1: "( (\<cn>  A) ) = ( 𝟬 \<cs> A )" by (rule MMI_df_neg)
   have S2: "( (\<cn>  B) ) = ( 𝟬 \<cs> B )" by (rule MMI_df_neg)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "( (\<cn>  A) ) = ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ ( 𝟬 \<cs> A ) = 
     ( 𝟬 \<cs> B )" by (rule MMI_eqeq12i)
   have S4: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from A1 have S5: "A ∈ ℂ".
   have S6: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from A2 have S7: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S6 S7 have S8: "( 𝟬 \<cs> B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_subcl)
   from S4 S5 S8 have S9: "( 𝟬 \<cs> A ) = ( 𝟬 \<cs> B ) ⟷ 
     ( A \<ca> ( 𝟬 \<cs> B ) ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_subadd)
   from S2 have S10: "( (\<cn>  B) ) = ( 𝟬 \<cs> B )" .
   from S10 have S11: "( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = ( A \<ca> ( 𝟬 \<cs> B ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_opreq2i)
   from A1 have S12: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S13: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S12 S13 have S14: "( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = ( A \<cs> B )" 
     by (rule MMI_negsub)
   from S11 S14 have S15: "( A \<ca> ( 𝟬 \<cs> B ) ) = ( A \<cs> B )" 
     by (rule MMI_eqtr3)
   from S15 have S16: "( A \<ca> ( 𝟬 \<cs> B ) ) = 𝟬 ⟷ ( A \<cs> B ) = 𝟬" 
     by (rule MMI_eqeq1i)
   from A1 have S17: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S18: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S17 S18 have S19: "( A \<cs> B ) = 𝟬 ⟷ A = B" by (rule MMI_subeq0)
   from S16 S19 have S20: "( A \<ca> ( 𝟬 \<cs> B ) ) = 𝟬 ⟷ A = B" 
     by (rule MMI_bitr)
   from S3 S9 S20 show "( (\<cn>  A) ) = ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ A = B" by (rule MMI_3bitr)
qed

(*********** 75-84****************************************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_negcon1: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( (\<cn>  A) ) = B ⟷ ( (\<cn>  B) ) = A"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S1 have S2: "( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) = A" by (rule MMI_negneg)
   from S2 have S3: "( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) = ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ A = ( (\<cn>  B) )" 
     by (rule MMI_eqeq1i)
   from A1 have S4: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S4 have S5: "( (\<cn>  A) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_negcl)
   from A2 have S6: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S5 S6 have S7: "( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) = 
     ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ ( (\<cn>  A) ) = B" by (rule MMI_neg11)
   have S8: "A = ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ ( (\<cn>  B) ) = A" by (rule MMI_eqcom)
   from S3 S7 S8 show "( (\<cn>  A) ) = B ⟷ ( (\<cn>  B) ) = A" by (rule MMI_3bitr3)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_negcon2: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "A = ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ B = ( (\<cn>  A) )"
proof -
   from A2 have S1: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A1 have S2: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "( (\<cn>  B) ) = A ⟷ ( (\<cn>  A) ) = B" 
     by (rule MMI_negcon1)
   have S4: "A = ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ ( (\<cn>  B) ) = A" by (rule MMI_eqcom)
   have S5: "B = ( (\<cn>  A) ) ⟷ ( (\<cn>  A) ) = B" by (rule MMI_eqcom)
   from S3 S4 S5 show "A = ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ B = ( (\<cn>  A) )" by (rule MMI_3bitr4)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_neg11t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) = ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ A = B )"
proof -
   have S1: "A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ ( (\<cn>  A) ) = 
     ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_negeq)
   from S1 have S2: "A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) = 
     ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) = ( (\<cn>  B) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   have S3: "A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ ( A = B ⟷ 
     if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = B )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) = ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ A = B ) ⟷ 
     ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) = ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ 
     if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = B ) )" by (rule MMI_bibi12d)
   have S5: "B = if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ ( (\<cn>  B) ) = 
     ( \<cn> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_negeq)
   from S5 have S6: "B = if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
     ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) = ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ 
     ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) = ( \<cn> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_eqeq2d)
   have S7: "B = if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = B ⟷ 
     if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq2)
   from S6 S7 have S8: "B = if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) = ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ 
     if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = B ) ⟷ ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) = 
     ( \<cn> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) ⟷ if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = 
     if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_bibi12d)
   have S9: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S9 have S10: "if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   have S11: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S11 have S12: "if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   from S10 S12 have S13: "( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) = 
     ( \<cn> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) ⟷ if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = 
     if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_neg11)
   from S4 S8 S13 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) = 
     ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ A = B )" by (rule MMI_dedth2h)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_negcon1t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) = B ⟷ ( (\<cn>  B) ) = A )"
proof -
   have S1: "( ( (\<cn>  A) ) ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) = 
     ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ ( (\<cn>  A) ) = B )" by (rule MMI_neg11t)
   have S2: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( (\<cn>  A) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_negclt)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) = 
     ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ ( (\<cn>  A) ) = B )" by (rule MMI_sylan)
   have S4: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) = A" by (rule MMI_negnegt)
   from S4 have S5: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) = A" 
     by (rule MMI_adantr)
   from S5 have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) = 
     ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ A = ( (\<cn>  B) ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   from S3 S6 have S7: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) = B ⟷ A = 
     ( (\<cn>  B) ) )" by (rule MMI_bitr3d)
   have S8: "A = ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ ( (\<cn>  B) ) = A" by (rule MMI_eqcom)
   from S7 S8 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) = B ⟷ 
     ( (\<cn>  B) ) = A )" by (rule MMI_syl6bb)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_negcon2t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A = ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ B = ( (\<cn>  A) ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) = B ⟷ ( (\<cn>  B) ) = A )" 
     by (rule MMI_negcon1t)
   have S2: "A = ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ ( (\<cn>  B) ) = A" by (rule MMI_eqcom)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A = ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ 
     ( (\<cn>  A) ) = B )" by (rule MMI_syl6rbbrA)
   have S4: "( (\<cn>  A) ) = B ⟷ B = ( (\<cn>  A) )" by (rule MMI_eqcom)
   from S3 S4 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A = ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⟷ B = 
     ( (\<cn>  A) ) )" by (rule MMI_syl6bb)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_subcant: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A \<cs> B ) = 
  ( A \<cs> C ) ⟷ B = C )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( \<cn> C ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) ⟷ 
     ( (\<cn>  B) ) = ( \<cn> C ) )" by (rule MMI_addcant)
   have S2: "C ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( \<cn> C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_negclt)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) ⟷ 
     ( (\<cn>  B) ) = ( \<cn> C ) )" by (rule MMI_syl3an3)
   have S4: "B ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_negclt)
   from S3 S4 have S5: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) ⟷ 
     ( (\<cn>  B) ) = ( \<cn> C ) )" by (rule MMI_syl3an2)
   have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = ( A \<cs> B )" 
     by (rule MMI_negsubt)
   from S6 have S7: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = ( A \<cs> B )" by (rule MMI_3adant3)
   have S8: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) = ( A \<cs> C )" 
     by (rule MMI_negsubt)
   from S8 have S9: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) = ( A \<cs> C )" by (rule MMI_3adant2)
   from S7 S9 have S10: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) ⟷ 
     ( A \<cs> B ) = ( A \<cs> C ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq12d)
   have S11: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( (\<cn>  B) ) = ( \<cn> C ) ⟷ B = C )" 
     by (rule MMI_neg11t)
   from S11 have S12: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( (\<cn>  B) ) = ( \<cn> C ) ⟷ B = C )" by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   from S5 S10 S12 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<cs> B ) = ( A \<cs> C ) ⟷ B = C )" by (rule MMI_3bitr3d)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_subcan2t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
  ( ( A \<cs> C ) = ( B \<cs> C ) ⟷ A = B )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) = ( A \<cs> C )" 
     by (rule MMI_negsubt)
   from S1 have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) = ( A \<cs> C )" by (rule MMI_3adant2)
   have S3: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( B \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) = ( B \<cs> C )" 
     by (rule MMI_negsubt)
   from S3 have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( B \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) = ( B \<cs> C )" by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   from S2 S4 have S5: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) = ( B \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) ⟷ ( A \<cs> C ) = 
     ( B \<cs> C ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq12d)
   have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ ( \<cn> C ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) = ( B \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) ⟷ A = B )" 
     by (rule MMI_addcan2t)
   have S7: "C ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( \<cn> C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_negclt)
   from S6 S7 have S8: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) = ( B \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) ⟷ A = B )" 
     by (rule MMI_syl3an3)
   from S5 S8 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<cs> C ) = ( B \<cs> C ) ⟷ A = B )" by (rule MMI_bitr3d)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_subcan: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( A \<cs> B ) = ( A \<cs> C ) ⟷ B = C"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A3 have S3: "C ∈ ℂ".
   have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A \<cs> B ) = ( A \<cs> C ) ⟷ B = C )" by (rule MMI_subcant)
   from S1 S2 S3 S4 show "( A \<cs> B ) = ( A \<cs> C ) ⟷ B = C" 
     by (rule MMI_mp3an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_subcan2: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( A \<cs> C ) = ( B \<cs> C ) ⟷ A = B"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A3 have S3: "C ∈ ℂ".
   have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<cs> C ) = ( B \<cs> C ) ⟷ A = B )" by (rule MMI_subcan2t)
   from S1 S2 S3 S4 show "( A \<cs> C ) = ( B \<cs> C ) ⟷ A = B" 
     by (rule MMI_mp3an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_subeq0t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A \<cs> B ) = 𝟬 ⟷ A = B )"
proof -
   have S1: "A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ ( A \<cs> B ) = 
     ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cs> B )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   from S1 have S2: "A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ ( ( A \<cs> B ) = 𝟬 ⟷ 
     ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cs> B ) = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   have S3: "A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ ( A = B ⟷ 
     if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = B )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A \<cs> B ) = 𝟬 ⟷ A = B ) ⟷ 
     ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cs> B ) = 𝟬 ⟷ 
     if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = B ) )" by (rule MMI_bibi12d)
   have S5: "B = if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
     ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cs> B ) = 
     ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cs> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   from S5 have S6: "B = if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
     ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cs> B ) = 𝟬 ⟷ 
     ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cs> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) = 𝟬 )" 
     by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   have S7: "B = if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = B ⟷ 
     if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq2)
   from S6 S7 have S8: "B = if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cs> B ) = 𝟬 ⟷ 
     if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = B ) ⟷ 
     ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cs> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) = 𝟬 ⟷ 
     if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_bibi12d)
   have S9: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S9 have S10: "if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   have S11: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S11 have S12: "if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   from S10 S12 have S13: 
     "( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cs> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) = 𝟬 ⟷ 
     if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 )" 
     by (rule MMI_subeq0)
   from S4 S8 S13 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<cs> B ) = 𝟬 ⟷ A = B )" by (rule MMI_dedth2h)
qed

(*******************85-90*******************************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_neg0: 
   shows "( \<cn> 𝟬 ) = 𝟬"
proof -
   have S1: "( \<cn> 𝟬 ) = ( 𝟬 \<cs> 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_df_neg)
   have S2: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S2 have S3: "( 𝟬 \<cs> 𝟬 ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_subid)
   from S1 S3 show "( \<cn> 𝟬 ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_eqtr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_renegcl: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "( (\<cn>  A) ) ∈ ℝ"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   have S2: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ ( ∃ x ∈ ℝ . ( A \<ca> x ) = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_axrnegex)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "∃ x ∈ ℝ . ( A \<ca> x ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_ax_mp)
   have S4: "( ∃ x ∈ ℝ . ( A \<ca> x ) = 𝟬 ) ⟷ 
     ( ∃ x . ( x ∈ ℝ ∧ ( A \<ca> x ) = 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_df_rex)
   from S3 S4 have S5: "∃ x . ( x ∈ ℝ ∧ ( A \<ca> x ) = 𝟬 )" 
     by (rule MMI_mpbi)
   { fix x
     have S6: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ x ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recnt)
     have S7: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
     from A1 have S8: "A ∈ ℝ".
     from S8 have S9: "A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
     have S10: "( 𝟬 ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ∧ x ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( 𝟬 \<cs> A ) = x ⟷ 
       ( A \<ca> x ) = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_subaddt)
     from S7 S9 S10 have S11: "x ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( ( 𝟬 \<cs> A ) = x ⟷ 
       ( A \<ca> x ) = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_mp3an12)
     from S6 S11 have S12: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ ( ( 𝟬 \<cs> A ) = x ⟷ 
       ( A \<ca> x ) = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_syl)
     have S13: "( (\<cn>  A) ) = ( 𝟬 \<cs> A )" by (rule MMI_df_neg)
     from S13 have S14: "( (\<cn>  A) ) = x ⟷ ( 𝟬 \<cs> A ) = x" 
       by (rule MMI_eqeq1i)
     from S12 S14 have S15: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) = x ⟷ 
       ( A \<ca> x ) = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_syl5bb)
     have S16: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) = x ⟶ ( (\<cn>  A) ) ∈ ℝ )" 
       by (rule MMI_eleq1a)
     from S15 S16 have S17: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ ( ( A \<ca> x ) = 𝟬 ⟶ 
       ( (\<cn>  A) ) ∈ ℝ )" by (rule MMI_sylbird)
     from S17 have "( x ∈ ℝ ∧ ( A \<ca> x ) = 𝟬 ) ⟶ ( (\<cn>  A) ) ∈ ℝ" 
       by (rule MMI_imp)
     } then have S18: 
	 "∀x . ( x ∈ ℝ ∧ ( A \<ca> x ) = 𝟬 ) ⟶ ( (\<cn>  A) ) ∈ ℝ" 
       by auto
   from S18 have S19: "( ∃ x . ( x ∈ ℝ ∧ ( A \<ca> x ) = 𝟬 ) ) ⟶ 
     ( (\<cn>  A) ) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_19_23aiv)
   from S5 S19 show "( (\<cn>  A) ) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax_mp)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_renegclt: 
   shows "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ ( (\<cn>  A) ) ∈ ℝ"
proof -
   have S1: "A = if ( A ∈ ℝ , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ ( (\<cn>  A) ) = 
     ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℝ , A , 𝟭 ) )" by (rule MMI_negeq)
   from S1 have S2: "A = if ( A ∈ ℝ , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) ∈ ℝ ⟷ 
     ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℝ , A , 𝟭 ) ) ∈ ℝ )" by (rule MMI_eleq1d)
   have S3: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   from S3 have S4: "if ( A ∈ ℝ , A , 𝟭 ) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   from S4 have S5: "( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℝ , A , 𝟭 ) ) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegcl)
   from S2 S5 show "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ ( (\<cn>  A) ) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_dedth)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_resubclt: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ ( A \<cs> B ) ∈ ℝ"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = ( A \<cs> B )" 
     by (rule MMI_negsubt)
   have S2: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recnt)
   have S3: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recnt)
   from S1 S2 S3 have S4: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
     ( A \<cs> B )" by (rule MMI_syl2an)
   have S5: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ∈ ℝ" 
     by (rule MMI_axaddrcl)
   have S6: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegclt)
   from S5 S6 have S7: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ∈ ℝ" 
     by (rule MMI_sylan2)
   from S4 S7 show "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ ( A \<cs> B ) ∈ ℝ" 
     by (rule MMI_eqeltrrd)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_resubcl: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "( A \<cs> B ) ∈ ℝ"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   have S3: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ ( A \<cs> B ) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_resubclt)
   from S1 S2 S3 show "( A \<cs> B ) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_mp2an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_0re: 
   shows "𝟬 ∈ ℝ"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from S1 have S2: "( 𝟭 \<cs> 𝟭 ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_subid)
   have S3: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S4: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   from S3 S4 have S5: "( 𝟭 \<cs> 𝟭 ) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_resubcl)
   from S2 S5 show "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_eqeltrr)
qed

(************** 91-95 ****************************************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mulid2t: 
   shows "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( 𝟭 ⋅ A ) = A"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   have S2: "( 𝟭 ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( 𝟭 ⋅ A ) = ( A ⋅ 𝟭 )" 
     by (rule MMI_axmulcom)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( 𝟭 ⋅ A ) = ( A ⋅ 𝟭 )" by (rule MMI_mpan)
   have S4: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( A ⋅ 𝟭 ) = A" by (rule MMI_ax1id)
   from S3 S4 show "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( 𝟭 ⋅ A ) = A" by (rule MMI_eqtrd)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mul12t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ ( B ⋅ C ) ) = 
  ( B ⋅ ( A ⋅ C ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ B ) = ( B ⋅ A )" 
     by (rule MMI_axmulcom)
   from S1 have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ C ) = ( ( B ⋅ A ) ⋅ C )" by (rule MMI_opreq1d)
   from S2 have S3: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ C ) = ( ( B ⋅ A ) ⋅ C )" by (rule MMI_3adant3)
   have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ C ) = ( A ⋅ ( B ⋅ C ) )" by (rule MMI_axmulass)
   have S5: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( B ⋅ A ) ⋅ C ) = ( B ⋅ ( A ⋅ C ) )" by (rule MMI_axmulass)
   from S5 have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( B ⋅ A ) ⋅ C ) = ( B ⋅ ( A ⋅ C ) )" by (rule MMI_3com12)
   from S3 S4 S6 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( A ⋅ ( B ⋅ C ) ) = ( B ⋅ ( A ⋅ C ) )" by (rule MMI_3eqtr3d)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mul23t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ C ) = 
  ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ B )"
proof -
   have S1: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( B ⋅ C ) = ( C ⋅ B )" 
     by (rule MMI_axmulcom)
   from S1 have S2: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ ( B ⋅ C ) ) = 
     ( A ⋅ ( C ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2d)
   from S2 have S3: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ ( B ⋅ C ) ) = 
     ( A ⋅ ( C ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ C ) = 
     ( A ⋅ ( B ⋅ C ) )" by (rule MMI_axmulass)
   have S5: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ B ) = 
     ( A ⋅ ( C ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_axmulass)
   from S5 have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ ( C ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_3com23)
   from S3 S4 S6 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ C ) = ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_3eqtr4d)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mul4t: 
   shows "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
  ( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ ( C ⋅ D ) ) = ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ ( B ⋅ D ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ C ) = ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_mul23t)
   from S1 have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ C ) ⋅ D ) = ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ B ) ⋅ D )" 
     by (rule MMI_opreq1d)
   from S2 have S3: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ C ) ⋅ D ) = ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ B ) ⋅ D )" 
     by (rule MMI_3expa)
   from S3 have S4: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ C ) ⋅ D ) = ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ B ) ⋅ D )" 
     by (rule MMI_adantrr)
   have S5: "( ( A ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ C ) ⋅ D ) = ( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ ( C ⋅ D ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_axmulass)
   from S5 have S6: "( ( A ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ C ) ⋅ D ) = ( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ ( C ⋅ D ) )" by (rule MMI_3expb)
   have S7: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axmulcl)
   from S6 S7 have S8: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ C ) ⋅ D ) = ( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ ( C ⋅ D ) )" by (rule MMI_sylan)
   have S9: "( ( A ⋅ C ) ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ B ) ⋅ D ) = ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ ( B ⋅ D ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_axmulass)
   from S9 have S10: "( ( A ⋅ C ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( B ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ B ) ⋅ D ) = ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ ( B ⋅ D ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_3expb)
   have S11: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axmulcl)
   from S10 S11 have S12: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( B ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ B ) ⋅ D ) = ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ ( B ⋅ D ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_sylan)
   from S12 have S13: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ B ) ⋅ D ) = ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ ( B ⋅ D ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_an4s)
   from S4 S8 S13 show "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ ( C ⋅ D ) ) = ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ ( B ⋅ D ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_3eqtr3d)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_muladdt: 
   shows "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
  ( ( A \<ca> B ) ⋅ ( C \<ca> D ) ) = 
  ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<ca> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "( ( A \<ca> B ) ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> B ) ⋅ ( C \<ca> D ) ) = 
     ( ( ( A \<ca> B ) ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( ( A \<ca> B ) ⋅ D ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_axdistr)
   have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<ca> B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axaddcl)
   from S2 have S3: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( A \<ca> B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S4: "( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ C ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_pm3_26)
   from S4 have S5: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ C ∈ ℂ" 
     by (rule MMI_adantl)
   have S6: "( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ D ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_pm3_27)
   from S6 have S7: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ D ∈ ℂ" 
     by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S1 S3 S5 S7 have S8: 
     "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶
     ( ( A \<ca> B ) ⋅ ( C \<ca> D ) ) = 
     ( ( ( A \<ca> B ) ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( ( A \<ca> B ) ⋅ D ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   have S9: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> B ) ⋅ C ) = ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ C ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_adddirt)
   from S9 have S10: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> B ) ⋅ C ) = ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ C ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_3expa)
   from S10 have S11: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> B ) ⋅ C ) = ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ C ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_adantrr)
   have S12: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> B ) ⋅ D ) = ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ D ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_adddirt)
   from S12 have S13: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> B ) ⋅ D ) = ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ D ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_3expa)
   from S13 have S14: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> B ) ⋅ D ) = ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ D ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_adantrl)
   from S11 S14 have S15: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A \<ca> B ) ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( ( A \<ca> B ) ⋅ D ) ) = 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ C ) ) \<ca> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ D ) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_opreq12d)
   have S16: 
     "( ( A ⋅ C ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( B ⋅ C ) ∈ ℂ ∧ 
     ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ D ) ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ C ) ) \<ca> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ D ) ) ) = 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ D ) ) ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ C ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_add23t)
   have S17: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axmulcl)
   from S17 have S18: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( A ⋅ C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_ad2ant2r)
   have S19: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( B ⋅ C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axmulcl)
   from S19 have S20: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( B ⋅ C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_adantrr)
   from S20 have S21: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( B ⋅ C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_adantll)
   have S22: "( ( A ⋅ D ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( B ⋅ D ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ D ) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axaddcl)
   have S23: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ D ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axmulcl)
   have S24: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( B ⋅ D ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axmulcl)
   from S22 S23 S24 have S25: 
     "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( B ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ D ) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_syl2an)
   from S25 have S26: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ D ) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_anandirs)
   from S26 have S27: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ D ) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_adantrl)
   from S16 S18 S21 S27 have S28: 
     "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ C ) ) \<ca> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ D ) ) ) = 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ D ) ) ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ C ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   have S29: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( B ⋅ D ) = ( D ⋅ B )" 
     by (rule MMI_axmulcom)
   from S29 have S30: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( B ⋅ D ) = ( D ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_ad2ant2l)
   from S30 have S31: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( A ⋅ D ) ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ D ) ) = 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( A ⋅ D ) ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_opreq2d)
   have S32: "( ( A ⋅ C ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( A ⋅ D ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( B ⋅ D ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( A ⋅ D ) ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ D ) ) = 
     ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ D ) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_axaddass)
   from S18 have S33: 
     "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ C ) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S23 have S34: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ D ) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S34 have S35: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( A ⋅ D ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_adantrl)
   from S35 have S36: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( A ⋅ D ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_adantlr)
   from S24 have S37: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( B ⋅ D ) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S37 have S38: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( B ⋅ D ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_ad2ant2l)
   from S32 S33 S36 S38 have S39: 
     "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( A ⋅ D ) ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ D ) ) = 
     ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ D ) ) )" by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   have S40: "( ( A ⋅ C ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( A ⋅ D ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( D ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( A ⋅ D ) ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) = 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<ca> ( A ⋅ D ) )" by (rule MMI_add23t)
   from S18 have S41: 
     "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ C ) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S36 have S42: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( A ⋅ D ) ∈ ℂ" .
   have S43: "( D ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( D ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axmulcl)
   from S43 have S44: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( D ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ" 
     by (rule MMI_ancoms)
   from S44 have S45: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( D ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_ad2ant2l)
   from S40 S41 S42 S45 have S46: 
     "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( A ⋅ D ) ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) = 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<ca> ( A ⋅ D ) )" by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   from S31 S39 S46 have S47: 
     "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ D ) ) ) = 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<ca> ( A ⋅ D ) )" by (rule MMI_3eqtr3d)
   have S48: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( B ⋅ C ) = ( C ⋅ B )" 
     by (rule MMI_axmulcom)
   from S48 have S49: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( B ⋅ C ) = ( C ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S49 have S50: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( B ⋅ C ) = ( C ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_an42s)
   from S47 S50 have S51: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ D ) ) ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ C ) ) = 
     ( ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<ca> ( A ⋅ D ) ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_opreq12d)
   have S52: 
     "( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( A ⋅ D ) ∈ ℂ ∧ 
     ( C ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<ca> ( A ⋅ D ) ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) = 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<ca> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_axaddass)
   have S53: "( ( A ⋅ C ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( D ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axaddcl)
   from S17 have S54: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ C ) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S44 have S55: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( D ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S53 S54 S55 have S56: 
     "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( B ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_syl2an)
   from S56 have S57: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_an4s)
   from S36 have S58: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( A ⋅ D ) ∈ ℂ" .
   have S59: "( C ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( C ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axmulcl)
   from S59 have S60: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( C ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ" 
     by (rule MMI_ancoms)
   from S60 have S61: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( C ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S61 have S62: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( C ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_an42s)
   from S52 S57 S58 S62 have S63: 
     "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<ca> ( A ⋅ D ) ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) = 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<ca> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   from S28 S51 S63 have S64: 
     "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ C ) ) \<ca> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( B ⋅ D ) ) ) = 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<ca> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_3eqtrd)
   from S8 S15 S64 show "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> B ) ⋅ ( C \<ca> D ) ) = 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<ca> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_3eqtrd)
qed

(********* 96-100****************************************************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_muladd11t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ⋅ ( 𝟭 \<ca> B ) ) = 
  ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) \<ca> ( B \<ca> ( A ⋅ B ) ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   have S2: "( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ∈ ℂ ∧ 𝟭 ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ⋅ ( 𝟭 \<ca> B ) ) = 
     ( ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ⋅ 𝟭 ) \<ca> ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ⋅ B ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_axdistr)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ⋅ ( 𝟭 \<ca> B ) ) = 
     ( ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ⋅ 𝟭 ) \<ca> ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ⋅ B ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_mp3an2)
   have S4: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   have S5: "( 𝟭 ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axaddcl)
   from S4 S5 have S6: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_mpan)
   from S3 S6 have S7: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ⋅ ( 𝟭 \<ca> B ) ) = 
     ( ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ⋅ 𝟭 ) \<ca> ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_sylan)
   from S6 have S8: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ∈ ℂ" .
   have S9: "( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ⋅ 𝟭 ) = ( 𝟭 \<ca> A )" 
     by (rule MMI_ax1id)
   from S8 S9 have S10: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ⋅ 𝟭 ) = ( 𝟭 \<ca> A )" 
     by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S10 have S11: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ⋅ 𝟭 ) = ( 𝟭 \<ca> A )" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S12: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   have S13: "( 𝟭 ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ⋅ B ) = 
     ( ( 𝟭 ⋅ B ) \<ca> ( A ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_adddirt)
   from S12 S13 have S14: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ⋅ B ) = ( ( 𝟭 ⋅ B ) \<ca> ( A ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_mp3an1)
   have S15: "B ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( 𝟭 ⋅ B ) = B" by (rule MMI_mulid2t)
   from S15 have S16: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( 𝟭 ⋅ B ) = B" 
     by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S16 have S17: 
     "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( 𝟭 ⋅ B ) \<ca> ( A ⋅ B ) ) = 
     ( B \<ca> ( A ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq1d)
   from S14 S17 have S18: 
     "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ⋅ B ) = 
     ( B \<ca> ( A ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_eqtrd)
   from S11 S18 have S19: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ⋅ 𝟭 ) \<ca> ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ⋅ B ) ) = 
     ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) \<ca> ( B \<ca> ( A ⋅ B ) ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq12d)
   from S7 S19 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) ⋅ ( 𝟭 \<ca> B ) ) = 
     ( ( 𝟭 \<ca> A ) \<ca> ( B \<ca> ( A ⋅ B ) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_eqtrd)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mul12: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( A ⋅ ( B ⋅ C ) ) = ( B ⋅ ( A ⋅ C ) )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "( A ⋅ B ) = ( B ⋅ A )" by (rule MMI_mulcom)
   from S3 have S4: "( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ C ) = ( ( B ⋅ A ) ⋅ C )" 
     by (rule MMI_opreq1i)
   from A1 have S5: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S6: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A3 have S7: "C ∈ ℂ".
   from S5 S6 S7 have S8: "( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ C ) = ( A ⋅ ( B ⋅ C ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_mulass)
   from A2 have S9: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A1 have S10: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A3 have S11: "C ∈ ℂ".
   from S9 S10 S11 have S12: "( ( B ⋅ A ) ⋅ C ) = ( B ⋅ ( A ⋅ C ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_mulass)
   from S4 S8 S12 show "( A ⋅ ( B ⋅ C ) ) = ( B ⋅ ( A ⋅ C ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_3eqtr3)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mul23: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ C ) = ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ B )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A3 have S3: "C ∈ ℂ".
   have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ C ) = 
     ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_mul23t)
   from S1 S2 S3 S4 show "( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ C ) = ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ B )" 
     by (rule MMI_mp3an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mul4: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℂ" and
    A4: "D ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ ( C ⋅ D ) ) = ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ ( B ⋅ D ) )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_pm3_2i)
   from A3 have S4: "C ∈ ℂ".
   from A4 have S5: "D ∈ ℂ".
   from S4 S5 have S6: "C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_pm3_2i)
   have S7: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ ( C ⋅ D ) ) = ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ ( B ⋅ D ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_mul4t)
   from S3 S6 S7 show "( ( A ⋅ B ) ⋅ ( C ⋅ D ) ) = ( ( A ⋅ C ) ⋅ ( B ⋅ D ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_mp2an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_muladd: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℂ" and
    A4: "D ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( ( A \<ca> B ) ⋅ ( C \<ca> D ) ) = 
  ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<ca> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_pm3_2i)
   from A3 have S4: "C ∈ ℂ".
   from A4 have S5: "D ∈ ℂ".
   from S4 S5 have S6: "C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_pm3_2i)
   have S7: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<ca> B ) ⋅ ( C \<ca> D ) ) =
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<ca> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_muladdt)
   from S3 S6 S7 show 
     "( ( A \<ca> B ) ⋅ ( C \<ca> D ) ) = 
     ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<ca> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_mp2an)
qed

(************ 101-110 *********************)
lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_subdit: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ ( B \<cs> C ) ) = ( ( A ⋅ B ) \<cs> ( A ⋅ C ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ∧ ( B \<cs> C ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ ( C \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) ) ) = 
     ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( A ⋅ ( B \<cs> C ) ) )" by (rule MMI_axdistr)
   have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3simp1)
   have S3: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ C ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3simp3)
   have S4: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( B \<cs> C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_subclt)
   from S4 have S5: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( B \<cs> C ) ∈ ℂ" 
     by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   from S1 S2 S3 S5 have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ ( C \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) ) ) = 
     ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( A ⋅ ( B \<cs> C ) ) )" by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   have S7: "( C ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( C \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) ) = B" by (rule MMI_pncan3t)
   from S7 have S8: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( C \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) ) = B" by (rule MMI_ancoms)
   from S8 have S9: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( C \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) ) = B" by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   from S9 have S10: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ ( C \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) ) ) = ( A ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_opreq2d)
   from S6 S10 have S11: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( A ⋅ ( B \<cs> C ) ) ) = ( A ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_eqtr3d)
   have S12: "( ( A ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( A ⋅ C ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( A ⋅ ( B \<cs> C ) ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( A ⋅ B ) \<cs> ( A ⋅ C ) ) = ( A ⋅ ( B \<cs> C ) ) ⟷ 
     ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( A ⋅ ( B \<cs> C ) ) ) = ( A ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_subaddt)
   have S13: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axmulcl)
   from S13 have S14: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ" 
     by (rule MMI_3adant3)
   have S15: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axmulcl)
   from S15 have S16: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ C ) ∈ ℂ" 
     by (rule MMI_3adant2)
   have S17: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ ( B \<cs> C ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ ( B \<cs> C ) ) ∈ ℂ" 
     by (rule MMI_axmulcl)
   from S4 have S18: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( B \<cs> C ) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S17 S18 have S19: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ ( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
     ( A ⋅ ( B \<cs> C ) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_sylan2)
   from S19 have S20: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
     ( A ⋅ ( B \<cs> C ) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3impb)
   from S12 S14 S16 S20 have S21: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( A ⋅ B ) \<cs> ( A ⋅ C ) ) = ( A ⋅ ( B \<cs> C ) ) ⟷ 
     ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( A ⋅ ( B \<cs> C ) ) ) = ( A ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   from S11 S21 have S22: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ B ) \<cs> ( A ⋅ C ) ) = ( A ⋅ ( B \<cs> C ) )" by (rule MMI_mpbird)
   from S22 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ ( B \<cs> C ) ) = ( ( A ⋅ B ) \<cs> ( A ⋅ C ) )" by (rule MMI_eqcomd)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_subdirt: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) ⋅ C ) = ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<cs> ( B ⋅ C ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "( C ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( C ⋅ ( A \<cs> B ) ) = ( ( C ⋅ A ) \<cs> ( C ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_subdit)
   from S1 have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( C ⋅ ( A \<cs> B ) ) = ( ( C ⋅ A ) \<cs> ( C ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_3coml)
   have S3: "( ( A \<cs> B ) ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) ⋅ C ) = ( C ⋅ ( A \<cs> B ) )" by (rule MMI_axmulcom)
   have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<cs> B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_subclt)
   from S3 S4 have S5: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) ⋅ C ) = ( C ⋅ ( A \<cs> B ) )" by (rule MMI_sylan)
   from S5 have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) ⋅ C ) = ( C ⋅ ( A \<cs> B ) )" by (rule MMI_3impa)
   have S7: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ C ) = ( C ⋅ A )" by (rule MMI_axmulcom)
   from S7 have S8: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ C ) = ( C ⋅ A )" 
     by (rule MMI_3adant2)
   have S9: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( B ⋅ C ) = ( C ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_axmulcom)
   from S9 have S10: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( B ⋅ C ) = ( C ⋅ B )" 
     by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   from S8 S10 have S11: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<cs> ( B ⋅ C ) ) = ( ( C ⋅ A ) \<cs> ( C ⋅ B ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_opreq12d)
   from S2 S6 S11 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) ⋅ C ) = ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<cs> ( B ⋅ C ) )" by (rule MMI_3eqtr4d)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_subdi: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( A ⋅ ( B \<cs> C ) ) = ( ( A ⋅ B ) \<cs> ( A ⋅ C ) )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A3 have S3: "C ∈ ℂ".
   have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ ( B \<cs> C ) ) = ( ( A ⋅ B ) \<cs> ( A ⋅ C ) )" by (rule MMI_subdit)
   from S1 S2 S3 S4 show "( A ⋅ ( B \<cs> C ) ) = ( ( A ⋅ B ) \<cs> ( A ⋅ C ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_mp3an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_subdir: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( ( A \<cs> B ) ⋅ C ) = ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<cs> ( B ⋅ C ) )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A3 have S3: "C ∈ ℂ".
   have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) ⋅ C ) = ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<cs> ( B ⋅ C ) )" by (rule MMI_subdirt)
   from S1 S2 S3 S4 show "( ( A \<cs> B ) ⋅ C ) = ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<cs> ( B ⋅ C ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_mp3an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mul01: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( A ⋅ 𝟬 ) = 𝟬"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   have S2: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   have S3: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S1 S2 S3 have S4: "( A ⋅ ( 𝟬 \<cs> 𝟬 ) ) = ( ( A ⋅ 𝟬 ) \<cs> ( A ⋅ 𝟬 ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_subdi)
   have S5: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S5 have S6: "( 𝟬 \<cs> 𝟬 ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_subid)
   from S6 have S7: "( A ⋅ ( 𝟬 \<cs> 𝟬 ) ) = ( A ⋅ 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_opreq2i)
   from A1 have S8: "A ∈ ℂ".
   have S9: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S8 S9 have S10: "( A ⋅ 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_mulcl)
   from S10 have S11: "( ( A ⋅ 𝟬 ) \<cs> ( A ⋅ 𝟬 ) ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_subid)
   from S4 S7 S11 show "( A ⋅ 𝟬 ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_3eqtr3)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mul02: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( 𝟬 ⋅ A ) = 𝟬"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from A1 have S2: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "( 𝟬 ⋅ A ) = ( A ⋅ 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_mulcom)
   from A1 have S4: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S4 have S5: "( A ⋅ 𝟬 ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_mul01)
   from S3 S5 show "( 𝟬 ⋅ A ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_eqtr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_1p1times: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( ( 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭 ) ⋅ A ) = ( A \<ca> A )"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   have S2: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from A1 have S3: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S1 S2 S3 have S4: "( ( 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭 ) ⋅ A ) = ( ( 𝟭 ⋅ A ) \<ca> ( 𝟭 ⋅ A ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_adddir)
   from A1 have S5: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S5 have S6: "( 𝟭 ⋅ A ) = A" by (rule MMI_mulid2)
   from S6 have S7: "( 𝟭 ⋅ A ) = A" .
   from S6 S7 have S8: "( ( 𝟭 ⋅ A ) \<ca> ( 𝟭 ⋅ A ) ) = ( A \<ca> A )" 
     by (rule MMI_opreq12i)
   from S4 S8 show "( ( 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭 ) ⋅ A ) = ( A \<ca> A )" 
     by (rule MMI_eqtr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mul01t: 
   shows "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( A ⋅ 𝟬 ) = 𝟬"
proof -
   have S1: "A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ 𝟬 ) = ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   from S1 have S2: "A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ 𝟬 ) = 𝟬 ⟷ ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ 𝟬 ) = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   have S3: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S3 have S4: "if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   from S4 have S5: "( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ 𝟬 ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_mul01)
   from S2 S5 show "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( A ⋅ 𝟬 ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_dedth)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mul02t: 
   shows "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( 𝟬 ⋅ A ) = 𝟬"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   have S2: "( 𝟬 ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( 𝟬 ⋅ A ) = ( A ⋅ 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_axmulcom)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( 𝟬 ⋅ A ) = ( A ⋅ 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_mpan)
   have S4: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( A ⋅ 𝟬 ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_mul01t)
   from S3 S4 show "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( 𝟬 ⋅ A ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_eqtrd)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mulneg1: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( ( (\<cn>  A) ) ⋅ B ) = ( \<cn> ( A ⋅ B ) )"
proof -
   from A2 have S1: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S1 have S2: "( B ⋅ 𝟬 ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_mul01)
   from A2 have S3: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A1 have S4: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S3 S4 have S5: "( B ⋅ A ) = ( A ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_mulcom)
   from S2 S5 have S6: "( ( B ⋅ 𝟬 ) \<cs> ( B ⋅ A ) ) = ( 𝟬 \<cs> ( A ⋅ B ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_opreq12i)
   have S7: "( (\<cn>  A) ) = ( 𝟬 \<cs> A )" by (rule MMI_df_neg)
   from S7 have S8: "( ( (\<cn>  A) ) ⋅ B ) = ( ( 𝟬 \<cs> A ) ⋅ B )" 
     by (rule MMI_opreq1i)
   have S9: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from A1 have S10: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S9 S10 have S11: "( 𝟬 \<cs> A ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_subcl)
   from A2 have S12: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S11 S12 have S13: "( ( 𝟬 \<cs> A ) ⋅ B ) = ( B ⋅ ( 𝟬 \<cs> A ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_mulcom)
   from A2 have S14: "B ∈ ℂ".
   have S15: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from A1 have S16: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S14 S15 S16 have 
     S17: "( B ⋅ ( 𝟬 \<cs> A ) ) = ( ( B ⋅ 𝟬 ) \<cs> ( B ⋅ A ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_subdi)
   from S8 S13 S17 have 
     S18: "( ( (\<cn>  A) ) ⋅ B ) = ( ( B ⋅ 𝟬 ) \<cs> ( B ⋅ A ) )" by (rule MMI_3eqtr)
   have S19: "( \<cn> ( A ⋅ B ) ) = ( 𝟬 \<cs> ( A ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_df_neg)
   from S6 S18 S19 show "( ( (\<cn>  A) ) ⋅ B ) = ( \<cn> ( A ⋅ B ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_3eqtr4)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mulneg2: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( A ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( A ⋅ B ) )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S2 have S3: "( (\<cn>  B) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_negcl)
   from S1 S3 have S4: "( A ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⋅ A )" by (rule MMI_mulcom)
   from A2 have S5: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A1 have S6: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S5 S6 have S7: "( ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⋅ A ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( B ⋅ A ) )" by (rule MMI_mulneg1)
   from A2 have S8: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A1 have S9: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S8 S9 have S10: "( B ⋅ A ) = ( A ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_mulcom)
   from S10 have S11: "( \<cn> ( B ⋅ A ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( A ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_negeqi)
   from S4 S7 S11 show "( A ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( A ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_3eqtr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mul2neg: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( ( (\<cn>  A) ) ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( A ⋅ B )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S2 have S3: "( (\<cn>  B) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_negcl)
   from S1 S3 have S4: "( ( (\<cn>  A) ) ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( A ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) )" by (rule MMI_mulneg1)
   from A1 have S5: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S3 have S6: "( (\<cn>  B) ) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S5 S6 have S7: "( A ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⋅ A )" by (rule MMI_mulcom)
   from A2 have S8: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A1 have S9: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S8 S9 have S10: "( ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⋅ A ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( B ⋅ A ) )" by (rule MMI_mulneg1)
   from S7 S10 have S11: "( A ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( B ⋅ A ) )" by (rule MMI_eqtr)
   from S11 have S12: "( \<cn> ( A ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( \<cn> ( B ⋅ A ) ) )" by (rule MMI_negeqi)
   from A2 have S13: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A1 have S14: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S13 S14 have S15: "( B ⋅ A ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_mulcl)
   from S15 have S16: "( \<cn> ( \<cn> ( B ⋅ A ) ) ) = 
 ( B ⋅ A )" by (rule MMI_negneg)
   from S4 S12 S16 have S17: "( ( (\<cn>  A) ) ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( B ⋅ A )" by (rule MMI_3eqtr)
   from A2 have S18: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A1 have S19: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S18 S19 have S20: "( B ⋅ A ) = ( A ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_mulcom)
   from S17 S20 show "( ( (\<cn>  A) ) ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( A ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_eqtr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_negdi: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( \<cn> ( A \<ca> B ) ) = 
 ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "( A \<ca> B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_addcl)
   from S3 have S4: "( 𝟭 ⋅ ( A \<ca> B ) ) = 
 ( A \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_mulid2)
   from S4 have S5: "( \<cn> ( 𝟭 ⋅ ( A \<ca> B ) ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( A \<ca> B ) )" by (rule MMI_negeqi)
   have S6: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from S6 have S7: "( \<cn> 𝟭 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_negcl)
   from A1 have S8: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S9: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S7 S8 S9 have S10: "( ( \<cn> 𝟭 ) ⋅ ( A \<ca> B ) ) = 
 ( ( ( \<cn> 𝟭 ) ⋅ A ) \<ca> ( ( \<cn> 𝟭 ) ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_adddi)
   have S11: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from S3 have S12: "( A \<ca> B ) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S11 S12 have S13: "( ( \<cn> 𝟭 ) ⋅ ( A \<ca> B ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( 𝟭 ⋅ ( A \<ca> B ) ) )" by (rule MMI_mulneg1)
   have S14: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from A1 have S15: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S14 S15 have S16: "( ( \<cn> 𝟭 ) ⋅ A ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( 𝟭 ⋅ A ) )" by (rule MMI_mulneg1)
   from A1 have S17: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S17 have S18: "( 𝟭 ⋅ A ) = A" by (rule MMI_mulid2)
   from S18 have S19: "( \<cn> ( 𝟭 ⋅ A ) ) = ( (\<cn>  A) )" by (rule MMI_negeqi)
   from S16 S19 have S20: "( ( \<cn> 𝟭 ) ⋅ A ) = ( (\<cn>  A) )" by (rule MMI_eqtr)
   have S21: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from A2 have S22: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S21 S22 have S23: "( ( \<cn> 𝟭 ) ⋅ B ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( 𝟭 ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_mulneg1)
   from A2 have S24: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S24 have S25: "( 𝟭 ⋅ B ) = B" by (rule MMI_mulid2)
   from S25 have S26: "( \<cn> ( 𝟭 ⋅ B ) ) = ( (\<cn>  B) )" by (rule MMI_negeqi)
   from S23 S26 have S27: "( ( \<cn> 𝟭 ) ⋅ B ) = ( (\<cn>  B) )" by (rule MMI_eqtr)
   from S20 S27 have S28: "( ( ( \<cn> 𝟭 ) ⋅ A ) \<ca> ( ( \<cn> 𝟭 ) ⋅ B ) ) = 
 ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq12i)
   from S10 S13 S28 have S29: "( \<cn> ( 𝟭 ⋅ ( A \<ca> B ) ) ) = 
 ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) )" by (rule MMI_3eqtr3)
   from S5 S29 show "( \<cn> ( A \<ca> B ) ) = 
 ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) )" by (rule MMI_eqtr3)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_negsubdi: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( \<cn> ( A \<cs> B ) ) = 
 ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) \<ca> B )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S2 have S3: "( (\<cn>  B) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_negcl)
   from S1 S3 have S4: "( \<cn> ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) = 
 ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) \<ca> ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) )" by (rule MMI_negdi)
   from A1 have S5: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S6: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S5 S6 have S7: "( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = ( A \<cs> B )" by (rule MMI_negsub)
   from S7 have S8: "( \<cn> ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( A \<cs> B ) )" by (rule MMI_negeqi)
   from A2 have S9: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S9 have S10: "( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = B" by (rule MMI_negneg)
   from S10 have S11: "( ( (\<cn>  A) ) \<ca> ( \<cn> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) = 
 ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_opreq2i)
   from S4 S8 S11 show "( \<cn> ( A \<cs> B ) ) = 
 ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_3eqtr3)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_negsubdi2: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( \<cn> ( A \<cs> B ) ) = ( B \<cs> A )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "( \<cn> ( A \<cs> B ) ) = 
 ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_negsubdi)
   from A1 have S4: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S4 have S5: "( (\<cn>  A) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_negcl)
   from A2 have S6: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S5 S6 have S7: "( ( (\<cn>  A) ) \<ca> B ) = 
 ( B \<ca> ( (\<cn>  A) ) )" by (rule MMI_addcom)
   from A2 have S8: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A1 have S9: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S8 S9 have S10: "( B \<ca> ( (\<cn>  A) ) ) = ( B \<cs> A )" by (rule MMI_negsub)
   from S3 S7 S10 show "( \<cn> ( A \<cs> B ) ) = ( B \<cs> A )" by (rule MMI_3eqtr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mulneg1t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) ⋅ B ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( A ⋅ B ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( (\<cn>  A) ) = 
 ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_negeq)
   from S1 have S2: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) ⋅ B ) = 
 ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_opreq1d)
   have S3: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ B ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   from S3 have S4: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( \<cn> ( A ⋅ B ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_negeqd)
   from S2 S4 have S5: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) ⋅ B ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( A ⋅ B ) ) ⟷ 
 ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ B ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ B ) ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq12d)
   have S6: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ B ) = 
 ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   have S7: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ B ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   from S7 have S8: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( \<cn> ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ B ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_negeqd)
   from S6 S8 have S9: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ B ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ B ) ) ⟷ 
 ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq12d)
   have S10: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S10 have S11: "if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   have S12: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S12 have S13: "if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   from S11 S13 have S14: "( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_mulneg1)
   from S5 S9 S14 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) ⋅ B ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( A ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_dedth2h)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mulneg2t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( A ⋅ B ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⋅ A ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( B ⋅ A ) )" by (rule MMI_mulneg1t)
   from S1 have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⋅ A ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( B ⋅ A ) )" by (rule MMI_ancoms)
   have S3: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⋅ A )" by (rule MMI_axmulcom)
   have S4: "B ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_negclt)
   from S3 S4 have S5: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( ( (\<cn>  B) ) ⋅ A )" by (rule MMI_sylan2)
   have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ B ) = ( B ⋅ A )" by (rule MMI_axmulcom)
   from S6 have S7: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( \<cn> ( A ⋅ B ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( B ⋅ A ) )" by (rule MMI_negeqd)
   from S2 S5 S7 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( A ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_3eqtr4d)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mulneg12t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶

 ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) ⋅ B ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( A ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_mulneg1t)
   have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( A ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_mulneg2t)
   from S1 S2 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) ⋅ B ) = 
 ( A ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) )" by (rule MMI_eqtr4d)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mul2negt: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( A ⋅ B )"
proof -
   have S1: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( (\<cn>  A) ) = 
 ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_negeq)
   from S1 have S2: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq1d)
   have S3: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ B ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( A ⋅ B ) ⟷ 
 ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq12d)
   have S5: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( (\<cn>  B) ) = 
 ( \<cn> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_negeq)
   from S5 have S6: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ ( \<cn> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2d)
   have S7: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ B ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   from S6 S7 have S8: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ B ) ⟷ 
 ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ ( \<cn> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq12d)
   have S9: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S9 have S10: "if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   have S11: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S11 have S12: "if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   from S10 S12 have S13: "( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ ( \<cn> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_mul2neg)
   from S4 S8 S13 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( A ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_dedth2h)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_negdit: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( \<cn> ( A \<ca> B ) ) = 
 ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<ca> B ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   from S1 have S2: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( \<cn> ( A \<ca> B ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<ca> B ) )" by (rule MMI_negeqd)
   have S3: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( (\<cn>  A) ) = 
 ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_negeq)
   from S3 have S4: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq1d)
   from S2 S4 have S5: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( \<cn> ( A \<ca> B ) ) = 
 ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ⟷ 
 ( \<cn> ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<ca> B ) ) = 
 ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq12d)
   have S6: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<ca> B ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<ca> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   from S6 have S7: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( \<cn> ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<ca> B ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<ca> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_negeqd)
   have S8: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( (\<cn>  B) ) = 
 ( \<cn> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_negeq)
   from S8 have S9: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = 
 ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) \<ca> ( \<cn> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2d)
   from S7 S9 have S10: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( \<cn> ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<ca> B ) ) = 
 ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ⟷ 
 ( \<cn> ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<ca> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) ) = 
 ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) \<ca> ( \<cn> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq12d)
   have S11: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S11 have S12: "if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   have S13: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S13 have S14: "if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   from S12 S14 have S15: "( \<cn> ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<ca> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) ) = 
 ( ( \<cn> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) \<ca> ( \<cn> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_negdi)
   from S5 S10 S15 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( \<cn> ( A \<ca> B ) ) = 
 ( ( (\<cn>  A) ) \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) )" by (rule MMI_dedth2h)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_negdi2t:

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_subsubt:
