   from S1 S5 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cs> ( B \<cs> C ) ) = ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> C )"
 by (rule MMI_eqtrd)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_subsub3t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cs> ( B \<cs> C ) ) = ( ( A \<ca> C ) \<cs> B )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cs> ( B \<cs> C ) ) = ( A \<ca> ( C \<cs> B ) )" by (rule MMI_subsub2t)
   have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> C ) \<cs> B ) = ( A \<ca> ( C \<cs> B ) )" by (rule MMI_addsubasst)
   from S2 have S3: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> C ) \<cs> B ) = ( A \<ca> ( C \<cs> B ) )" by (rule MMI_3com23)
   from S1 S3 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cs> ( B \<cs> C ) ) = ( ( A \<ca> C ) \<cs> B )"
 by (rule MMI_eqtr4d)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_subsub4t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<cs> C ) = ( A \<cs> ( B \<ca> C ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ ( \<cn> C ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cs> ( B \<cs> ( \<cn> C ) ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) )" by (rule MMI_subsubt)
   have S2: "C ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( \<cn> C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_negclt)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cs> ( B \<cs> ( \<cn> C ) ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) )" by (rule MMI_syl3an3)
   have S4: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( B \<cs> ( \<cn> C ) ) = ( B \<ca> C )" by (rule MMI_subnegt)
   from S4 have S5: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( B \<cs> ( \<cn> C ) ) = ( B \<ca> C )" by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   from S5 have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cs> ( B \<cs> ( \<cn> C ) ) ) = 
 ( A \<cs> ( B \<ca> C ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2d)
   have S7: "( ( A \<cs> B ) ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<cs> C )" by (rule MMI_negsubt)
   have S8: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<cs> B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_subclt)
   from S7 S8 have S9: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<cs> C )" by (rule MMI_sylan)
   from S9 have S10: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<cs> C )" by (rule MMI_3impa)
   from S3 S6 S10 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<cs> C ) = ( A \<cs> ( B \<ca> C ) )"
 by (rule MMI_3eqtr3rd)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_sub23t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<cs> C ) = ( ( A \<cs> C ) \<cs> B )"
proof -
   have S1: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( B \<ca> C ) = ( C \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_axaddcom)
   from S1 have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( B \<ca> C ) = ( C \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   from S2 have S3: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cs> ( B \<ca> C ) ) = ( A \<cs> ( C \<ca> B ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2d)
   have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<cs> C ) = ( A \<cs> ( B \<ca> C ) )" by (rule MMI_subsub4t)
   have S5: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> C ) \<cs> B ) = ( A \<cs> ( C \<ca> B ) )" by (rule MMI_subsub4t)
   from S5 have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> C ) \<cs> B ) = ( A \<cs> ( C \<ca> B ) )" by (rule MMI_3com23)
   from S3 S4 S6 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<cs> C ) = ( ( A \<cs> C ) \<cs> B )"
 by (rule MMI_3eqtr4d)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_nnncant: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> ( B \<cs> C ) ) \<cs> C ) = ( A \<cs> B )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ ( B \<cs> C ) ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> ( B \<cs> C ) ) \<cs> C ) = 
 ( A \<cs> ( ( B \<cs> C ) \<ca> C ) )" by (rule MMI_subsub4t)
   have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3simp1)
   have S3: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( B \<cs> C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_subclt)
   from S3 have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( B \<cs> C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   have S5: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ C ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3simp3)
   from S1 S2 S4 S5 have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> ( B \<cs> C ) ) \<cs> C ) = 
 ( A \<cs> ( ( B \<cs> C ) \<ca> C ) )" by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   have S7: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( B \<cs> C ) \<ca> C ) = B" by (rule MMI_npcant)
   from S7 have S8: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cs> ( ( B \<cs> C ) \<ca> C ) ) = ( A \<cs> B )" by (rule MMI_opreq2d)
   from S8 have S9: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cs> ( ( B \<cs> C ) \<ca> C ) ) = ( A \<cs> B )" by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   from S6 S9 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> ( B \<cs> C ) ) \<cs> C ) = ( A \<cs> B )"
 by (rule MMI_eqtrd)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_nnncan1t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<cs> ( A \<cs> C ) ) = ( C \<cs> B )"
proof -
   have S1: "( ( A \<cs> B ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( A \<cs> C ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> ( \<cn> ( A \<cs> C ) ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<cs> ( A \<cs> C ) )" by (rule MMI_negsubt)
   have S2: "( ( A \<cs> B ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( \<cn> ( A \<cs> C ) ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> ( \<cn> ( A \<cs> C ) ) ) = 
 ( ( \<cn> ( A \<cs> C ) ) \<ca> ( A \<cs> B ) )" by (rule MMI_axaddcom)
   have S3: "( A \<cs> C ) ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( \<cn> ( A \<cs> C ) ) ∈ ℂ" 
     by (rule MMI_negclt)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "( ( A \<cs> B ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( A \<cs> C ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<ca> ( \<cn> ( A \<cs> C ) ) ) = 
 ( ( \<cn> ( A \<cs> C ) ) \<ca> ( A \<cs> B ) )" by (rule MMI_sylan2)
   from S1 S4 have S5: "( ( A \<cs> B ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( A \<cs> C ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<cs> ( A \<cs> C ) ) = 
 ( ( \<cn> ( A \<cs> C ) ) \<ca> ( A \<cs> B ) )" by (rule MMI_eqtr3d)
   have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<cs> B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_subclt)
   from S6 have S7: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cs> B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3adant3)
   have S8: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<cs> C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_subclt)
   from S8 have S9: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cs> C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3adant2)
   from S5 S7 S9 have S10: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<cs> ( A \<cs> C ) ) = 
 ( ( \<cn> ( A \<cs> C ) ) \<ca> ( A \<cs> B ) )" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   have S11: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( \<cn> ( A \<cs> C ) ) = ( C \<cs> A )" by (rule MMI_negsubdi2t)
   from S11 have S12: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( \<cn> ( A \<cs> C ) ) = ( C \<cs> A )" by (rule MMI_3adant2)
   from S12 have S13: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( \<cn> ( A \<cs> C ) ) \<ca> ( A \<cs> B ) ) = 
 ( ( C \<cs> A ) \<ca> ( A \<cs> B ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq1d)
   have S14: "( C ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( C \<cs> A ) \<ca> ( A \<cs> B ) ) = ( C \<cs> B )" by (rule MMI_npncant)
   from S14 have S15: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( C \<cs> A ) \<ca> ( A \<cs> B ) ) = ( C \<cs> B )" by (rule MMI_3coml)
   from S10 S13 S15 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) \<cs> ( A \<cs> C ) ) = ( C \<cs> B )"
 by (rule MMI_3eqtrd)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_nnncan2t:

 ( ( A \<cs> ( B \<cs> C ) ) \<cs> C ) = 
 ( ( A \<cs> C ) \<cs> ( B \<cs> C ) )" by (rule MMI_sub23t)
   have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3simp1)
   have S3: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( B \<cs> C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_subclt)
   from S3 have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( B \<cs> C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   have S5: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ C ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3simp3)
   from S1 S2 S4 S5 have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> ( B \<cs> C ) ) \<cs> C ) = 
 ( ( A \<cs> C ) \<cs> ( B \<cs> C ) )" by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   have S7: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> ( B \<cs> C ) ) \<cs> C ) = ( A \<cs> B )" by (rule MMI_nnncant)
   from S6 S7 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> C ) \<cs> ( B \<cs> C ) ) = ( A \<cs> B )" by (rule MMI_eqtr3d)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_nncant: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cs> ( A \<cs> B ) ) = B"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ 𝟬 ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> 𝟬 ) \<cs> ( A \<cs> B ) ) = ( B \<cs> 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_nnncan1t)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> 𝟬 ) \<cs> ( A \<cs> B ) ) = ( B \<cs> 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_mp3an2)
   have S4: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( A \<cs> 𝟬 ) = A" by (rule MMI_subid1t)
   from S4 have S5: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<cs> 𝟬 ) = A" 
     by (rule MMI_adantr)
   from S5 have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> 𝟬 ) \<cs> ( A \<cs> B ) ) = 
 ( A \<cs> ( A \<cs> B ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq1d)
   have S7: "B ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( B \<cs> 𝟬 ) = B" by (rule MMI_subid1t)
   from S7 have S8: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( B \<cs> 𝟬 ) = B" 
     by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S3 S6 S8 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cs> ( A \<cs> B ) ) = B" by (rule MMI_3eqtr3d)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_nppcan2t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> ( B \<ca> C ) ) \<ca> C ) = ( A \<cs> B )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ ( B \<ca> C ) ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cs> ( ( B \<ca> C ) \<cs> C ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<cs> ( B \<ca> C ) ) \<ca> C )" by (rule MMI_subsubt)
   have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3simp1)
   have S3: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( B \<ca> C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axaddcl)
   from S3 have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( B \<ca> C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   have S5: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ C ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3simp3)
   from S1 S2 S4 S5 have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cs> ( ( B \<ca> C ) \<cs> C ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<cs> ( B \<ca> C ) ) \<ca> C )" by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   have S7: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( B \<ca> C ) \<cs> C ) = B" by (rule MMI_pncant)
   from S7 have S8: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( B \<ca> C ) \<cs> C ) = B" by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   from S8 have S9: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cs> ( ( B \<ca> C ) \<cs> C ) ) = ( A \<cs> B )" by (rule MMI_opreq2d)
   from S6 S9 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> ( B \<ca> C ) ) \<ca> C ) = ( A \<cs> B )" by (rule MMI_eqtr3d)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mulm1t: 
   shows "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( ( \<cn> 𝟭 ) ⋅ A ) = ( (\<cn>  A) )"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   have S2: "( 𝟭 ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( \<cn> 𝟭 ) ⋅ A ) = ( \<cn> ( 𝟭 ⋅ A ) )" by (rule MMI_mulneg1t)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
 ( ( \<cn> 𝟭 ) ⋅ A ) = ( \<cn> ( 𝟭 ⋅ A ) )" by (rule MMI_mpan)
   have S4: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( 𝟭 ⋅ A ) = A" by (rule MMI_mulid2t)
   from S4 have S5: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( \<cn> ( 𝟭 ⋅ A ) ) = ( (\<cn>  A) )" 
     by (rule MMI_negeqd)
   from S3 S5 show "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( ( \<cn> 𝟭 ) ⋅ A ) = ( (\<cn>  A) )" 
     by (rule MMI_eqtrd)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mulm1: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( ( \<cn> 𝟭 ) ⋅ A ) = ( (\<cn>  A) )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   have S2: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( ( \<cn> 𝟭 ) ⋅ A ) = ( (\<cn>  A) )" by (rule MMI_mulm1t)
   from S1 S2 show "( ( \<cn> 𝟭 ) ⋅ A ) = ( (\<cn>  A) )" by (rule MMI_ax_mp)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_sub4t: 
   shows "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( C \<ca> D ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<cs> C ) \<ca> ( B \<cs> D ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( \<cn> ( C \<ca> D ) ) = 
 ( ( \<cn> C ) \<ca> ( \<cn> D ) )" by (rule MMI_negdit)
   from S1 have S2: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( \<cn> ( C \<ca> D ) ) = 
 ( ( \<cn> C ) \<ca> ( \<cn> D ) )" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S2 have S3: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<ca> ( \<cn> ( C \<ca> D ) ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<ca> ( ( \<cn> C ) \<ca> ( \<cn> D ) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_opreq2d)
   have S4: 
     "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( ( \<cn> C ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( \<cn> D ) ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<ca> ( ( \<cn> C ) \<ca> ( \<cn> D ) ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) \<ca> ( B \<ca> ( \<cn> D ) ) )" by (rule MMI_add4t)
   have S5: "C ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( \<cn> C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_negclt)
   have S6: "D ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( \<cn> D ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_negclt)
   from S5 S6 have S7: "( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( \<cn> C ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( \<cn> D ) ∈ ℂ )" by (rule MMI_anim12i)
   from S4 S7 have S8: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<ca> ( ( \<cn> C ) \<ca> ( \<cn> D ) ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) \<ca> ( B \<ca> ( \<cn> D ) ) )" by (rule MMI_sylan2)
   from S3 S8 have S9: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<ca> ( \<cn> ( C \<ca> D ) ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) \<ca> ( B \<ca> ( \<cn> D ) ) )" by (rule MMI_eqtrd)
   have S10: "( ( A \<ca> B ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( C \<ca> D ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<ca> ( \<cn> ( C \<ca> D ) ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( C \<ca> D ) )" by (rule MMI_negsubt)
   have S11: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<ca> B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axaddcl)
   have S12: "( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( C \<ca> D ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axaddcl)
   from S10 S11 S12 have S13: 
     "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<ca> ( \<cn> ( C \<ca> D ) ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( C \<ca> D ) )" by (rule MMI_syl2an)
   have S14: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) = ( A \<cs> C )" by (rule MMI_negsubt)
   from S14 have S15: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) = ( A \<cs> C )" by (rule MMI_ad2ant2r)
   have S16: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( B \<ca> ( \<cn> D ) ) = ( B \<cs> D )" by (rule MMI_negsubt)
   from S16 have S17: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( B \<ca> ( \<cn> D ) ) = ( B \<cs> D )" by (rule MMI_ad2ant2l)
   from S15 S17 have S18: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) \<ca> ( B \<ca> ( \<cn> D ) ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<cs> C ) \<ca> ( B \<cs> D ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq12d)
   from S9 S13 S18 show "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( C \<ca> D ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<cs> C ) \<ca> ( B \<cs> D ) )" by (rule MMI_3eqtr3d)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_sub4: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℂ" and
    A4: "D ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( C \<ca> D ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<cs> C ) \<ca> ( B \<cs> D ) )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_pm3_2i)
   from A3 have S4: "C ∈ ℂ".
   from A4 have S5: "D ∈ ℂ".
   from S4 S5 have S6: "C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_pm3_2i)
   have S7: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( C \<ca> D ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<cs> C ) \<ca> ( B \<cs> D ) )" by (rule MMI_sub4t)
   from S3 S6 S7 show "( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( C \<ca> D ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<cs> C ) \<ca> ( B \<cs> D ) )" by (rule MMI_mp2an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mulsubt: 
   shows "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) ⋅ ( C \<cs> D ) ) = 
 ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<cs> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = ( A \<cs> B )" by (rule MMI_negsubt)
   have S2: "( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( C \<ca> ( \<cn> D ) ) = ( C \<cs> D )" by (rule MMI_negsubt)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ⋅ ( C \<ca> ( \<cn> D ) ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) ⋅ ( C \<cs> D ) )" by (rule MMI_opreqan12d)
   have S4: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ ( \<cn> D ) ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ⋅ ( C \<ca> ( \<cn> D ) ) ) = 
 ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( ( \<cn> D ) ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) \<ca> ( ( A ⋅ ( \<cn> D ) ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) )" by (rule MMI_muladdt)
   have S5: "D ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( \<cn> D ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_negclt)
   from S4 S5 have S6: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ⋅ ( C \<ca> ( \<cn> D ) ) ) = 
 ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( ( \<cn> D ) ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) \<ca> 
     ( ( A ⋅ ( \<cn> D ) ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) )" by (rule MMI_sylanr2)
   have S7: "B ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_negclt)
   from S6 S7 have S8: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ⋅ ( C \<ca> ( \<cn> D ) ) ) = 
 ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( ( \<cn> D ) ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) 
     \<ca> ( ( A ⋅ ( \<cn> D ) ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_sylanl2)
   have S9: "( D ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( \<cn> D ) ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = ( D ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_mul2negt)
   from S9 have S10: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( \<cn> D ) ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = ( D ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_ancoms)
   from S10 have S11: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( ( \<cn> D ) ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) = 
 ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2d)
   from S11 have S12: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( ( \<cn> D ) ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) = 
 ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_ad2ant2l)
   have S13: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ ( \<cn> D ) ) = ( \<cn> ( A ⋅ D ) )" by (rule MMI_mulneg2t)
   have S14: "( C ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( C ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) = ( \<cn> ( C ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_mulneg2t)
   from S13 S14 have S15: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ ( \<cn> D ) ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) = 
 ( ( \<cn> ( A ⋅ D ) ) \<ca> ( \<cn> ( C ⋅ B ) ) )" by (rule MMI_opreqan12d)
   have S16: "( ( A ⋅ D ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( C ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( \<cn> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) ) = 
 ( ( \<cn> ( A ⋅ D ) ) \<ca> ( \<cn> ( C ⋅ B ) ) )" by (rule MMI_negdit)
   have S17: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ D ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axmulcl)
   have S18: "( C ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( C ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axmulcl)
   from S16 S17 S18 have S19: 
     "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( \<cn> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) ) = 
 ( ( \<cn> ( A ⋅ D ) ) \<ca> ( \<cn> ( C ⋅ B ) ) )" by (rule MMI_syl2an)
   from S15 S19 have S20: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ ( \<cn> D ) ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) )" by (rule MMI_eqtr4d)
   from S20 have S21: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ ( \<cn> D ) ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) )" by (rule MMI_ancom2s)
   from S21 have S22: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ ( \<cn> D ) ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) = 
 ( \<cn> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) )" by (rule MMI_an42s)
   from S12 S22 have S23: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( ( \<cn> D ) ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) \<ca> 
     ( ( A ⋅ ( \<cn> D ) ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ) ) = 
 ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<ca> ( \<cn> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> 
     ( C ⋅ B ) ) ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq12d)
   have S24: "( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> 
     ( C ⋅ B ) ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<ca> ( \<cn> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) ) ) = 
 ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<cs> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_negsubt)
   have S25: "( ( A ⋅ C ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( D ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axaddcl)
   have S26: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axmulcl)
   have S27: "( D ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( D ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axmulcl)
   from S27 have S28: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( D ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ" 
     by (rule MMI_ancoms)
   from S25 S26 S28 have S29: 
     "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( B ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_syl2an)
   from S29 have S30: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_an4s)
   have S31: "( ( A ⋅ D ) ∈ ℂ ∧ ( C ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axaddcl)
   from S17 have S32: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ D ) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S18 have S33: "( C ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( C ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S33 have S34: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( C ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ" 
     by (rule MMI_ancoms)
   from S31 S32 S34 have S35: 
     "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_syl2an)
   from S35 have S36: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_an42s)
   from S24 S30 S36 have S37: 
     "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<ca> ( \<cn> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) ) ) = 
 ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<cs> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   from S8 S23 S37 have S38: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> ( (\<cn>  B) ) ) ⋅ ( C \<ca> ( \<cn> D ) ) ) = 
 ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<cs> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_3eqtrd)
   from S3 S38 show "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> B ) ⋅ ( C \<cs> D ) ) = 
 ( ( ( A ⋅ C ) \<ca> ( D ⋅ B ) ) \<cs> ( ( A ⋅ D ) \<ca> ( C ⋅ B ) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_eqtr3d)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_pnpcant: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( A \<ca> C ) ) = ( B \<cs> C )"
proof -
   have S1: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( A \<ca> C ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<cs> A ) \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) )" by (rule MMI_sub4t)
   from S1 have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ ( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( A \<ca> C ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<cs> A ) \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) )" by (rule MMI_anandis)
   have S3: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( A \<cs> A ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_subidt)
   from S3 have S4: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> A ) \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) ) = 
 ( 𝟬 \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq1d)
   have S5: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( B \<cs> C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_subclt)
   have S6: "( B \<cs> C ) ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
 ( 𝟬 \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) ) = ( B \<cs> C )" by (rule MMI_addid2t)
   from S5 S6 have S7: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( 𝟬 \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) ) = ( B \<cs> C )" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S4 S7 have S8: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ ( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cs> A ) \<ca> ( B \<cs> C ) ) = ( B \<cs> C )" by (rule MMI_sylan9eq)
   from S2 S8 have S9: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ ( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( A \<ca> C ) ) = ( B \<cs> C )" by (rule MMI_eqtrd)
   from S9 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( A \<ca> C ) ) = ( B \<cs> C )" by (rule MMI_3impb)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_pnpcan2t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> C ) \<cs> ( B \<ca> C ) ) = ( A \<cs> B )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<ca> C ) = ( C \<ca> A )" by (rule MMI_axaddcom)
   from S1 have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<ca> C ) = ( C \<ca> A )" by (rule MMI_3adant2)
   have S3: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( B \<ca> C ) = ( C \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_axaddcom)
   from S3 have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( B \<ca> C ) = ( C \<ca> B )" by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   from S2 S4 have S5: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> C ) \<cs> ( B \<ca> C ) ) = 
 ( ( C \<ca> A ) \<cs> ( C \<ca> B ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq12d)
   have S6: "( C ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( C \<ca> A ) \<cs> ( C \<ca> B ) ) = ( A \<cs> B )" by (rule MMI_pnpcant)
   from S6 have S7: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( C \<ca> A ) \<cs> ( C \<ca> B ) ) = ( A \<cs> B )" by (rule MMI_3coml)
   from S5 S7 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> C ) \<cs> ( B \<ca> C ) ) = ( A \<cs> B )" by (rule MMI_eqtrd)
qed

(*******141-150*********************************)
lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_pnncant: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( A \<cs> C ) ) = ( B \<ca> C )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ ( \<cn> C ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) ) = 
 ( B \<cs> ( \<cn> C ) )" by (rule MMI_pnpcant)
   have S2: "C ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( \<cn> C ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_negclt)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) ) = 
 ( B \<cs> ( \<cn> C ) )" by (rule MMI_syl3an3)
   have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) = ( A \<cs> C )" by (rule MMI_negsubt)
   from S4 have S5: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) = ( A \<cs> C )" by (rule MMI_3adant2)
   from S5 have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( A \<ca> ( \<cn> C ) ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( A \<cs> C ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2d)
   have S7: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( B \<cs> ( \<cn> C ) ) = ( B \<ca> C )" by (rule MMI_subnegt)
   from S7 have S8: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( B \<cs> ( \<cn> C ) ) = ( B \<ca> C )" by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   from S3 S6 S8 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( A \<cs> C ) ) = ( B \<ca> C )" by (rule MMI_3eqtr3d)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_ppncant: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<ca> ( C \<cs> B ) ) = ( A \<ca> C )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<ca> B ) = ( B \<ca> A )" by (rule MMI_axaddcom)
   from S1 have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<ca> B ) = ( B \<ca> A )" by (rule MMI_3adant3)
   from S2 have S3: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( B \<cs> C ) ) = 
 ( ( B \<ca> A ) \<cs> ( B \<cs> C ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq1d)
   have S4: "( ( A \<ca> B ) ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( B \<cs> C ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<ca> ( C \<cs> B ) )" by (rule MMI_subsub2t)
   have S5: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A \<ca> B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axaddcl)
   from S5 have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<ca> B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3adant3)
   have S7: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3simp2)
   have S8: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ C ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3simp3)
   from S4 S6 S7 S8 have S9: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( B \<cs> C ) ) = 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<ca> ( C \<cs> B ) )" by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   have S10: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( B \<ca> A ) \<cs> ( B \<cs> C ) ) = ( A \<ca> C )" by (rule MMI_pnncant)
   from S10 have S11: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( B \<ca> A ) \<cs> ( B \<cs> C ) ) = ( A \<ca> C )" by (rule MMI_3com12)
   from S3 S9 S11 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<ca> ( C \<cs> B ) ) = ( A \<ca> C )" by (rule MMI_3eqtr3d)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_pnncan: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( A \<cs> C ) ) = ( B \<ca> C )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A3 have S3: "C ∈ ℂ".
   have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( A \<cs> C ) ) = ( B \<ca> C )" by (rule MMI_pnncant)
   from S1 S2 S3 S4 show "( ( A \<ca> B ) \<cs> ( A \<cs> C ) ) = ( B \<ca> C )" by (rule MMI_mp3an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mulcan: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℂ" and
    A4: "A ≠ 𝟬"   
   shows "( A ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ C ) ⟷ B = C"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A4 have S2: "A ≠ 𝟬".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "∃ x ∈ ℂ . ( A ⋅ x ) = 𝟭" by (rule MMI_recex)
   from A1 have S4: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S5: "B ∈ ℂ".
   { fix x
     have S6: "( x ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
       ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ B ) = ( x ⋅ ( A ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_axmulass)
     from S5 S6 have S7: "( x ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
       ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ B ) = ( x ⋅ ( A ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_mp3an3)
     from A3 have S8: "C ∈ ℂ".
     have S9: "( x ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
       ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ C ) = ( x ⋅ ( A ⋅ C ) )" by (rule MMI_axmulass)
     from S8 S9 have S10: "( x ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
       ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ C ) = ( x ⋅ ( A ⋅ C ) )" by (rule MMI_mp3an3)
     from S7 S10 have S11: "( x ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
       ( ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ B ) = 
       ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ C ) ⟷ 
       ( x ⋅ ( A ⋅ B ) ) = 
       ( x ⋅ ( A ⋅ C ) ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq12d)
     from S4 S11 have S12: "x ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
       ( ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ B ) = 
       ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ C ) ⟷ 
       ( x ⋅ ( A ⋅ B ) ) = 
       ( x ⋅ ( A ⋅ C ) ) )" by (rule MMI_mpan2)
     have S13: 
       "( A ⋅ B ) =  ( A ⋅ C ) ⟶ 
       ( x ⋅ ( A ⋅ B ) ) = ( x ⋅ ( A ⋅ C ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
     from S12 S13 have S14: "x ∈ ℂ ⟶  
       ( ( A ⋅ B ) =  ( A ⋅ C ) ⟶  ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ B ) = 
       ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ C ) )" by (rule MMI_syl5bir)
     from S14 have S15: 
       "( x ∈ ℂ ∧ ( A ⋅ x ) =  𝟭 ) ⟶  ( ( A ⋅ B ) = 
       ( A ⋅ C ) ⟶  ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ B ) = 
       ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ C ) )" by (rule MMI_adantr)
     from A1 have S16: "A ∈ ℂ".
     have S17: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ x ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
       ( A ⋅ x ) = ( x ⋅ A )" by (rule MMI_axmulcom)
     from S16 S17 have S18: "x ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( A ⋅ x ) = ( x ⋅ A )" 
       by (rule MMI_mpan)
     from S18 have S19: "x ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
       ( ( A ⋅ x ) = 𝟭 ⟷ ( x ⋅ A ) = 𝟭 )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
     have S20: "( x ⋅ A ) = 
       𝟭 ⟶ ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ B ) = ( 𝟭 ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
     from A2 have S21: "B ∈ ℂ".
     from S21 have S22: "( 𝟭 ⋅ B ) = B" by (rule MMI_mulid2)
     from S20 S22 have S23: "( x ⋅ A ) = 𝟭 ⟶ ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ B ) = B" 
       by (rule MMI_syl6eq)
     have S24: "( x ⋅ A ) = 
       𝟭 ⟶ ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ C ) = ( 𝟭 ⋅ C )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
     from A3 have S25: "C ∈ ℂ".
     from S25 have S26: "( 𝟭 ⋅ C ) = C" by (rule MMI_mulid2)
     from S24 S26 have S27: "( x ⋅ A ) = 𝟭 ⟶ ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ C ) = C" 
       by (rule MMI_syl6eq)
     from S23 S27 have S28: "( x ⋅ A ) =  𝟭 ⟶ 
       ( ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ B ) = 
       ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ C ) ⟷ B = C )" by (rule MMI_eqeq12d)
     from S19 S28 have S29: "x ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
       ( ( A ⋅ x ) =  𝟭 ⟶ 
       ( ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ B ) = 
       ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ C ) ⟷ B = C ) )" by (rule MMI_syl6bi)
     from S29 have S30: 
       "( x ∈ ℂ ∧ ( A ⋅ x ) = 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
       ( ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ B ) = 
       ( ( x ⋅ A ) ⋅ C ) ⟷ B = C )" by (rule MMI_imp)
     from S15 S30 have S31: 
       "( x ∈ ℂ ∧ ( A ⋅ x ) = 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
       ( ( A ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ C ) ⟶ B = C )" by (rule MMI_sylibd)
     from S31 have "x ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
       ( ( A ⋅ x ) = 𝟭 ⟶  ( ( A ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ C ) ⟶ B = C ) )" 
       by (rule MMI_ex)
     } then have  S32: "∀ x. x ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
       ( ( A ⋅ x ) = 𝟭 ⟶  ( ( A ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ C ) ⟶ B = C ) )" 
       by auto
     from S32 have S33: "( ∃ x ∈ ℂ . ( A ⋅ x ) =  𝟭 ) ⟶ 
       ( ( A ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ C ) ⟶ B = C )" by (rule MMI_r19_23aiv)
     from S3 S33 have S34: "( A ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ C ) ⟶ B = C" 
       by (rule MMI_ax_mp)
     have S35: "B = C ⟶ ( A ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ C )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
     from S34 S35 show "( A ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ C ) ⟷ B = C" by (rule MMI_impbi)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mulcant2: assumes A1: "A ≠ 𝟬"   
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ C ) ⟷ B = C )"
proof -
   have S1: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ B ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   have S2: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ C ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ C )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ B ) = 
 ( A ⋅ C ) ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ B ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ C ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq12d)
   from S3 have S4: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( A ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ C ) ⟷ B = C ) ⟷ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ B ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ C ) ⟷ 
 B = C ) )" by (rule MMI_bibi1d)
   have S5: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ B ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟭 ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   from S5 have S6: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ B ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ C ) ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟭 ) ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ C ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   have S7: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( B = C ⟷ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟭 ) = C )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1)
   from S6 S7 have S8: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ B ) = ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ C ) ⟷ B = C ) ⟷ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟭 ) ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ C ) ⟷ 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟭 ) = C ) )" by (rule MMI_bibi12d)
   have S9: "C = 
 if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ C ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟭 ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   from S9 have S10: "C = 
 if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟭 ) ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ C ) ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟭 ) ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟭 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq2d)
   have S11: "C = 
 if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟭 ) = 
 C ⟷ 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟭 ) = 
 if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟭 ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq2)
   from S10 S11 have S12: "C = 
 if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟭 ) ) = ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ C ) ⟷ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟭 ) = C ) ⟷ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟭 ) ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟭 ) ) ⟷ 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟭 ) = 
 if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟭 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_bibi12d)
   have S13: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from S13 have S14: "if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   have S15: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from S15 have S16: "if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟭 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   have S17: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from S17 have S18: "if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟭 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   have S19: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( A ≠ 𝟬 ⟷ if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ≠ 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_neeq1)
   have S20: "𝟭 = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( 𝟭 ≠ 𝟬 ⟷ if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ≠ 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_neeq1)
   from A1 have S21: "A ≠ 𝟬".
   have S22: "𝟭 ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_ax1ne0)
   from S19 S20 S21 S22 have S23: "if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_keephyp)
   from S14 S16 S18 S23 have S24: "( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟭 ) ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟭 ) ) ⟷ 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟭 ) = 
 if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟭 )" by (rule MMI_mulcan)
   from S4 S8 S12 S24 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ C ) ⟷ B = C )" by (rule MMI_dedth3h)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mulcant: 
   shows "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ C ) ⟷ B = C )"
proof -
   have S1: "A = 
 if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( A ∈ ℂ ⟷ if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ∈ ℂ )" by (rule MMI_eleq1)
   have S2: "A = 
 if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( B ∈ ℂ ⟷ B ∈ ℂ )" by (rule MMI_pm4_2i)
   have S3: "A = 
 if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( C ∈ ℂ ⟷ C ∈ ℂ )" by (rule MMI_pm4_2i)
   from S1 S2 S3 have S4: "A = 
 if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) )" by (rule MMI_3anbi123d)
   have S5: "A = 
 if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ B ) = 
 ( if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   have S6: "A = 
 if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ C ) = 
 ( if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ C )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   from S5 S6 have S7: "A = 
 if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ B ) = 
 ( A ⋅ C ) ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ B ) = 
 ( if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ C ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq12d)
   from S7 have S8: "A = 
 if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( A ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ C ) ⟷ B = C ) ⟷ 
 ( ( if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ B ) = 
 ( if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ C ) ⟷ 
 B = C ) )" by (rule MMI_bibi1d)
   from S4 S8 have S9: "A = 
 if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( ( A ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ C ) ⟷ B = C ) ) ⟷ 
 ( ( if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ B ) = 
 ( if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ C ) ⟷ 
 B = C ) ) )" by (rule MMI_imbi12d)
   have S10: "if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_elimne0)
   from S10 have S11: "( if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ B ) = 
 ( if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ C ) ⟷ B = C )" by (rule MMI_mulcant2)
   from S9 S11 have S12: "A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
 ( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ C ) ⟷ B = C ) )" by (rule MMI_dedth)
   from S12 show "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ C ) ⟷ B = C )" by (rule MMI_impcom)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mulcan2t: 
   shows "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ∧ C ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ C ) = ( B ⋅ C ) ⟷ A = B )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ C ) = ( C ⋅ A )" by (rule MMI_axmulcom)
   from S1 have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ C ) = ( C ⋅ A )" by (rule MMI_3adant2)
   have S3: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( B ⋅ C ) = ( C ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_axmulcom)
   from S3 have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( B ⋅ C ) = ( C ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   from S2 S4 have S5: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ C ) = 
 ( B ⋅ C ) ⟷ ( C ⋅ A ) = ( C ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq12d)
   from S5 have S6: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ∧ C ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ C ) = 
 ( B ⋅ C ) ⟷ ( C ⋅ A ) = ( C ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S7: "( ( C ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ∧ C ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( C ⋅ A ) = ( C ⋅ B ) ⟷ A = B )" by (rule MMI_mulcant)
   from S7 have S8: "( C ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( C ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
 ( ( C ⋅ A ) = ( C ⋅ B ) ⟷ A = B ) )" by (rule MMI_ex)
   from S8 have S9: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( C ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
 ( ( C ⋅ A ) = ( C ⋅ B ) ⟷ A = B ) )" by (rule MMI_3coml)
   from S9 have S10: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ∧ C ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( C ⋅ A ) = ( C ⋅ B ) ⟷ A = B )" by (rule MMI_imp)
   from S6 S10 show "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ∧ C ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ C ) = ( B ⋅ C ) ⟷ A = B )" by (rule MMI_bitrd)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mul0or: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( A ⋅ B ) = 𝟬 ⟷ ( A = 𝟬 ∨ B = 𝟬 )"
proof -
   have S1: "A ≠ 𝟬 ⟷ ¬ ( A = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_df_ne)
   from A1 have S2: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S3: "B ∈ ℂ".
   have S4: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S2 S3 S4 have S5: "A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ 𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3pm3_2i)
   have S6: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ 𝟬 ∈ ℂ ) ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ 𝟬 ) ⟷ B = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_mulcant)
   from S5 S6 have S7: "A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ 𝟬 ) ⟷ B = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_mpan)
   from A1 have S8: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S8 have S9: "( A ⋅ 𝟬 ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_mul01)
   from S9 have S10: "( A ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ 𝟬 ) ⟷ ( A ⋅ B ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_eqeq2i)
   from S7 S10 have S11: "A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( ( A ⋅ B ) = 𝟬 ⟷ B = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_syl5bbr)
   from S11 have S12: "A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( ( A ⋅ B ) = 𝟬 ⟶ B = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_biimpd)
   from S1 S12 have S13: "¬ ( A = 
 𝟬 ) ⟶ ( ( A ⋅ B ) = 𝟬 ⟶ B = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_sylbir)
   from S13 have S14: "( A ⋅ B ) = 
 𝟬 ⟶ ( ¬ ( A = 𝟬 ) ⟶ B = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_com12)
   from S14 have S15: "( A ⋅ B ) = 𝟬 ⟶ ( A = 𝟬 ∨ B = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_orrd)
   have S16: "A = 𝟬 ⟶ ( A ⋅ B ) = ( 𝟬 ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   from A2 have S17: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from S17 have S18: "( 𝟬 ⋅ B ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_mul02)
   from S16 S18 have S19: "A = 𝟬 ⟶ ( A ⋅ B ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_syl6eq)
   have S20: "B = 𝟬 ⟶ ( A ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   from S9 have S21: "( A ⋅ 𝟬 ) = 𝟬" .
   from S20 S21 have S22: "B = 𝟬 ⟶ ( A ⋅ B ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_syl6eq)
   from S19 S22 have S23: "( A = 𝟬 ∨ B = 𝟬 ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ B ) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_jaoi)
   from S15 S23 show "( A ⋅ B ) = 𝟬 ⟷ ( A = 𝟬 ∨ B = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_impbi)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_msq0: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "( A ⋅ A ) = 𝟬 ⟷ A = 𝟬"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A1 have S2: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "( A ⋅ A ) = 𝟬 ⟷ ( A = 𝟬 ∨ A = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_mul0or)
   have S4: "( A = 𝟬 ∨ A = 𝟬 ) ⟷ A = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_oridm)
   from S3 S4 show "( A ⋅ A ) = 𝟬 ⟷ A = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_bitr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mul0ort: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ B ) = 𝟬 ⟷ ( A = 𝟬 ∨ B = 𝟬 ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ B ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   from S1 have S2: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ B ) = 
 𝟬 ⟷ ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ B ) = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   have S3: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( A = 𝟬 ⟷ if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1)
   from S3 have S4: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A = 𝟬 ∨ B = 𝟬 ) ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = 𝟬 ∨ B = 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_orbi1d)
   from S2 S4 have S5: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( A ⋅ B ) = 𝟬 ⟷ ( A = 𝟬 ∨ B = 𝟬 ) ) ⟷ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ B ) = 
 𝟬 ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = 
 𝟬 ∨ B = 𝟬 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_bibi12d)
   have S6: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ B ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   from S6 have S7: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ B ) = 
 𝟬 ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   have S8: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( B = 𝟬 ⟷ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1)
   from S8 have S9: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = 𝟬 ∨ B = 𝟬 ) ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = 
 𝟬 ∨ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) = 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_orbi2d)
   from S7 S9 have S10: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ B ) = 𝟬 ⟷ ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = 𝟬 ∨ B = 𝟬 ) ) ⟷ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 𝟬 ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = 
 𝟬 ∨ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) = 𝟬 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_bibi12d)
   have S11: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S11 have S12: "if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   have S13: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S13 have S14: "if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   from S12 S14 have S15: "( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 𝟬 ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) = 
 𝟬 ∨ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_mul0or)
   from S5 S10 S15 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ B ) = 𝟬 ⟷ ( A = 𝟬 ∨ B = 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_dedth2h)
qed

(********* 151-153**************************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_muln0bt: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ≠ 𝟬 ∧ B ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟷ ( A ⋅ B ) ≠ 𝟬 )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ B ) = 𝟬 ⟷ ( A = 𝟬 ∨ B = 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_mul0ort)
   from S1 have S2: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ¬ ( ( A ⋅ B ) = 𝟬 ) ⟷ 
 ¬ ( ( A = 𝟬 ∨ B = 𝟬 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_negbid)
   have S3: "¬ ( ( A = 𝟬 ∨ B = 𝟬 ) ) ⟷ 
 ( ¬ ( A = 𝟬 ) ∧ ¬ ( B = 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_ioran)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ¬ ( A = 𝟬 ) ∧ ¬ ( B = 𝟬 ) ) ⟷ 
 ¬ ( ( A ⋅ B ) = 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_syl6rbb)
   have S5: "A ≠ 𝟬 ⟷ ¬ ( A = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_df_ne)
   have S6: "B ≠ 𝟬 ⟷ ¬ ( B = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_df_ne)
   from S5 S6 have S7: "( A ≠ 𝟬 ∧ B ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟷ 
 ( ¬ ( A = 𝟬 ) ∧ ¬ ( B = 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_anbi12i)
   have S8: "( A ⋅ B ) ≠ 𝟬 ⟷ ¬ ( ( A ⋅ B ) = 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_df_ne)
   from S4 S7 S8 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ≠ 𝟬 ∧ B ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟷ ( A ⋅ B ) ≠ 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_3bitr4g)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_muln0: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ" and
    A3: "A ≠ 𝟬" and
    A4: "B ≠ 𝟬"   
   shows "( A ⋅ B ) ≠ 𝟬"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A3 have S3: "A ≠ 𝟬".
   from A4 have S4: "B ≠ 𝟬".
   from S3 S4 have S5: "A ≠ 𝟬 ∧ B ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_pm3_2i)
   have S6: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ≠ 𝟬 ∧ B ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟷ ( A ⋅ B ) ≠ 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_muln0bt)
   from S5 S6 have S7: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ B ) ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_mpbii)
   from S1 S2 S7 show "( A ⋅ B ) ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_mp2an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_receu: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ" and
    A3: "A ≠ 𝟬"   
   shows "∃! x . x ∈ ℂ ∧ ( A ⋅ x ) = B"
proof -
  { fix x y
    have S1: "x = y ⟶ ( A ⋅ x ) = ( A ⋅ y )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
    from S1 have S2: "x = y ⟶ ( ( A ⋅ x ) = B ⟷ ( A ⋅ y ) = B )" 
      by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
  } then have S2: "∀ x y. x = y ⟶ ( ( A ⋅ x ) = B ⟷ ( A ⋅ y ) = B )"
    by simp
    from S2 have S3: 
      "( ∃! x . x ∈ ℂ ∧ ( A ⋅ x ) =  B ) ⟷ 
      ( ( ∃ x ∈ ℂ . ( A ⋅ x ) = B ) ∧ 
      ( ∀ x ∈ ℂ . ∀ y ∈ ℂ . ( ( ( A ⋅ x ) = B ∧ ( A ⋅ y ) = B ) ⟶ x = y ) ) )" 
      by (rule MMI_reu4)
    from A1 have S4: "A ∈ ℂ".
    from A3 have S5: "A ≠ 𝟬".
   from S4 S5 have S6: "∃ y ∈ ℂ . ( A ⋅ y ) = 𝟭" by (rule MMI_recex)
   from A2 have S7: "B ∈ ℂ".
   { fix y
     have S8: "( y ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ ( y ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_axmulcl)
     from S7 S8 have S9: "y ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( y ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_mpan2)
     have S10: "( y ⋅ B ) ∈ ℂ ⟷ 
       ( ∃ x ∈ ℂ . x = ( y ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_risset)
     from S9 S10 have S11: "y ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( ∃ x ∈ ℂ . x = ( y ⋅ B ) )" 
       by (rule MMI_sylib)
     { fix x
       have S12: "x =  ( y ⋅ B ) ⟶ 
	 ( A ⋅ x ) = ( A ⋅ ( y ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
       from A1 have S13: "A ∈ ℂ".
       from A2 have S14: "B ∈ ℂ".
       have S15: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ y ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
	 ( ( A ⋅ y ) ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ ( y ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_axmulass)
       from S13 S14 S15 have S16: "y ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
	 ( ( A ⋅ y ) ⋅ B ) = ( A ⋅ ( y ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_mp3an13)
       from S16 have S17: "y ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
	 ( A ⋅ ( y ⋅ B ) ) = ( ( A ⋅ y ) ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_eqcomd)
       from S12 S17 have S18: "( y ∈ ℂ ∧ x = 
	 ( y ⋅ B ) ) ⟶ 
	 ( A ⋅ x ) = ( ( A ⋅ y ) ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_sylan9eqr)
       have S19: "( A ⋅ y ) = 
	 𝟭 ⟶ ( ( A ⋅ y ) ⋅ B ) = ( 𝟭 ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
       from A2 have S20: "B ∈ ℂ".
       from S20 have S21: "( 𝟭 ⋅ B ) = B" by (rule MMI_mulid2)
       from S19 S21 have S22: "( A ⋅ y ) = 𝟭 ⟶ ( ( A ⋅ y ) ⋅ B ) = B" 
	 by (rule MMI_syl6eq)
       from S18 S22 have S23: 
	 "( ( A ⋅ y ) = 𝟭 ∧ ( y ∈ ℂ ∧ x = 
	 ( y ⋅ B ) ) ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ x ) = B" by (rule MMI_sylan9eqr)
       from S23 have S24: 
	 "( A ⋅ y ) = 𝟭 ⟶  ( y ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
	 ( x = ( y ⋅ B ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ x ) = B ) )" by (rule MMI_exp32)
       from S24 have S25: "( y ∈ ℂ ∧ ( A ⋅ y ) = 
	 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
	 ( x = ( y ⋅ B ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ x ) = B )" by (rule MMI_impcom)
       from S25 have
	 "( y ∈ ℂ ∧ ( A ⋅ y ) = 𝟭 ) ⟶ ( x ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
	 ( x = ( y ⋅ B ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ x ) = B ) )" by (rule MMI_a1d)
       } then have S26: 
	 "∀ x . ( y ∈ ℂ ∧ ( A ⋅ y ) = 𝟭 ) ⟶ ( x ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
	 ( x = ( y ⋅ B ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ x ) = B ) )" by simp
       from S26 have S27: 
	 "( y ∈ ℂ ∧ ( A ⋅ y ) = 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
	 ( ∀ x ∈ ℂ . ( x = ( y ⋅ B ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ x ) = B ) )" by (rule MMI_r19_21aiv)
       from S27 have S28: "y ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
	 ( ( A ⋅ y ) =	𝟭 ⟶ 
	 ( ∀ x ∈ ℂ . ( x = ( y ⋅ B ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ x ) = B ) ) )" by (rule MMI_ex)
       have S29: "( ∀ x ∈ ℂ . ( x = ( y ⋅ B ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ x ) = B ) ) ⟶ 
	 ( ( ∃ x ∈ ℂ . x = ( y ⋅ B ) ) ⟶ 
	 ( ∃ x ∈ ℂ . ( A ⋅ x ) = B ) )" by (rule MMI_r19_22)
       from S28 S29 have S30: 
	 "y ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( ( A ⋅ y ) =  𝟭 ⟶ 
	 ( ( ∃ x ∈ ℂ . x = ( y ⋅ B ) ) ⟶ 
	 ( ∃ x ∈ ℂ . ( A ⋅ x ) = B ) ) )" by (rule MMI_syl6)
       from S11 S30 have 
	 "y ∈ ℂ ⟶  ( ( A ⋅ y ) =  𝟭 ⟶ ( ∃ x ∈ ℂ . ( A ⋅ x ) = B ) )" 
	 by (rule MMI_mpid)
       } then have S31: 
	   "∀ y . y ∈ ℂ ⟶  ( ( A ⋅ y ) =  𝟭 ⟶ ( ∃ x ∈ ℂ . ( A ⋅ x ) = B ) )" 
	 by simp
       from S31 have S32: "( ∃ y ∈ ℂ . ( A ⋅ y ) = 
	 𝟭 ) ⟶ ( ∃ x ∈ ℂ . ( A ⋅ x ) = B )" by (rule MMI_r19_23aiv)
       from S6 S32 have S33: "∃ x ∈ ℂ . ( A ⋅ x ) = B" by (rule MMI_ax_mp)
       from A1 have S34: "A ∈ ℂ".
       from A3 have S35: "A ≠ 𝟬".
       { fix x y
	 from S35 have S36: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ x ∈ ℂ ∧ y ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
	   ( ( A ⋅ x ) = ( A ⋅ y ) ⟷ x = y )" by (rule MMI_mulcant2)
	 have S37: 
	   "( ( A ⋅ x ) =   B ∧ ( A ⋅ y ) = 
	   B ) ⟶ ( A ⋅ x ) = ( A ⋅ y )" by (rule MMI_eqtr3t)
	 from S36 S37 have S38: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ x ∈ ℂ ∧ y ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
	   ( ( ( A ⋅ x ) = B ∧ ( A ⋅ y ) = B ) ⟶ 
	   x = y )" by (rule MMI_syl5bi)
	 from S34 S38 have "( x ∈ ℂ ∧ y ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
	   ( ( ( A ⋅ x ) = B ∧ ( A ⋅ y ) = B ) ⟶ 
	   x = y )" by (rule MMI_mp3an1)
       } then have  S39: "∀ x y. ( x ∈ ℂ ∧ y ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
	   ( ( ( A ⋅ x ) = B ∧ ( A ⋅ y ) = B ) ⟶ 
	   x = y )" by auto
       from S39 have S40: 
	 "∀ x ∈ ℂ . ∀ y ∈ ℂ . ( ( ( A ⋅ x ) = B ∧ ( A ⋅ y ) = B ) ⟶ 
	 x = y )" by (rule MMI_rgen2)
       from S3 S33 S40 show "∃! x . x ∈ ℂ ∧ ( A ⋅ x ) = B" by (rule MMI_mpbir2an)
qed

(** this is proven by definition rather than importing the Metamath proof **)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_divval: assumes "A ∈ ℂ"  "B ∈ ℂ" "B ≠ 𝟬"
  shows "A \<cdiv> B =  ⋃ { x ∈ ℂ . B ⋅ x = A }"
  using cdiv_def by simp

(****** 154-160***********************************)


lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_divmul: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℂ" and
    A4: "B ≠ 𝟬"   
   shows "( A \<cdiv> B ) = C ⟷ ( B ⋅ C ) = A"
proof -
   from A3 have S1: "C ∈ ℂ".
   { fix x
     have S2: "x = 
       C ⟶ ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = x ⟷ ( A \<cdiv> B ) = C )" by (rule MMI_eqeq2)
     have S3: "x = C ⟶ ( B ⋅ x ) = ( B ⋅ C )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
     from S3 have S4: "x = 
       C ⟶ ( ( B ⋅ x ) = A ⟷ ( B ⋅ C ) = A )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
     from S2 S4 have  
       "x = C ⟶ 
       ( ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = x ⟷ ( B ⋅ x ) = A ) ⟷ 
       ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = C ⟷ ( B ⋅ C ) = A ) )" by (rule MMI_bibi12d)
   } then have S5: "∀x. x = C ⟶ 
       ( ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = x ⟷ ( B ⋅ x ) = A ) ⟷ 
       ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = C ⟷ ( B ⋅ C ) = A ) )"
     by simp
   from A2 have S6: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A1 have S7: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A4 have S8: "B ≠ 𝟬".
   from S6 S7 S8 have S9: "∃! x . x ∈ ℂ ∧ ( B ⋅ x ) = A" by (rule MMI_receu)
   { fix x
     have S10: "( x ∈ ℂ ∧ ( ∃! x . x ∈ ℂ ∧ ( B ⋅ x ) = A ) ) ⟶ 
       ( ( B ⋅ x ) = 
       A ⟷ ⋃ { x ∈ ℂ . ( B ⋅ x ) = A } = x )" by (rule MMI_reuuni1)
     from S9 S10 have  
       "x ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( ( B ⋅ x ) =  A ⟷ ⋃ { x ∈ ℂ . ( B ⋅ x ) = A } = x )" 
       by (rule MMI_mpan2)
   } then have S11: 
       "∀ x. x ∈ ℂ ⟶ ( ( B ⋅ x ) =  A ⟷ ⋃ { x ∈ ℂ . ( B ⋅ x ) = A } = x )" 
     by blast
   from A1 have S12: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S13: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A4 have S14: "B ≠ 𝟬".
   from S12 S13 S14 have S15: "( A \<cdiv> B ) = 
     ⋃ { x ∈ ℂ . ( B ⋅ x ) = A }" by (rule MMI_divval)
   from S15 have S16: "∀ x. ( A \<cdiv> B ) = 
     x ⟷ ⋃ { x ∈ ℂ . ( B ⋅ x ) = A } = x" by simp(*rule MMI_eqeq1i*)
   from S11 S16 have S17: "∀ x. x ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = x ⟷ ( B ⋅ x ) = A )" by (rule MMI_syl6rbbr)
   from S5 S17 have S18: "C ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
     ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = C ⟷ ( B ⋅ C ) = A )" by (rule MMI_vtoclga)
   from S1 S18 show "( A \<cdiv> B ) = C ⟷ ( B ⋅ C ) = A" by (rule MMI_ax_mp)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_divmulz: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "B ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = C ⟷ ( B ⋅ C ) = A )"
proof -
   have S1: "B = 
 if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cdiv> B ) = 
 ( A \<cdiv> if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   from S1 have S2: "B = 
 if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = 
 C ⟷ ( A \<cdiv> if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) ) = C )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   have S3: "B = 
 if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( B ⋅ C ) = 
 ( if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) ⋅ C )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   from S3 have S4: "B = 
 if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( B ⋅ C ) = 
 A ⟷ ( if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) ⋅ C ) = A )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   from S2 S4 have S5: "B = 
 if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = C ⟷ ( B ⋅ C ) = A ) ⟷ 
 ( ( A \<cdiv> if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) ) = 
 C ⟷ 
 ( if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) ⋅ C ) = A ) )" by (rule MMI_bibi12d)
   from A1 have S6: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S7: "B ∈ ℂ".
   have S8: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from S7 S8 have S9: "if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_keepel)
   from A3 have S10: "C ∈ ℂ".
   have S11: "if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_elimne0)
   from S6 S9 S10 S11 have S12: "( A \<cdiv> if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) ) = 
 C ⟷ ( if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) ⋅ C ) = A" by (rule MMI_divmul)
   from S5 S12 show "B ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = C ⟷ ( B ⋅ C ) = A )" by (rule MMI_dedth)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_divmult: 
   shows "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ∧ B ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = C ⟷ ( B ⋅ C ) = A )"
proof -
   have S1: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cdiv> B ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> B )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   from S1 have S2: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = 
 C ⟷ ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> B ) = C )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   have S3: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( B ⋅ C ) = 
 A ⟷ ( B ⋅ C ) = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq2)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = C ⟷ ( B ⋅ C ) = A ) ⟷ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> B ) = 
 C ⟷ 
 ( B ⋅ C ) = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_bibi12d)
   from S4 have S5: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( B ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = C ⟷ ( B ⋅ C ) = A ) ) ⟷ 
 ( B ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> B ) = 
 C ⟷ 
 ( B ⋅ C ) = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ) )" by (rule MMI_imbi2d)
   have S6: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( B ≠ 𝟬 ⟷ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ≠ 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_neeq1)
   have S7: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> B ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   from S7 have S8: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> B ) = 
 C ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 C )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   have S9: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( B ⋅ C ) = 
 ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⋅ C )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   from S9 have S10: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( B ⋅ C ) = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟷ 
 ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⋅ C ) = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   from S8 S10 have S11: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> B ) = C ⟷ ( B ⋅ C ) = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⟷ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 C ⟷ 
 ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⋅ C ) = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_bibi12d)
   from S6 S11 have S12: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( B ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> B ) = C ⟷ ( B ⋅ C ) = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ) ⟷ 
 ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 C ⟷ 
 ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⋅ C ) = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ) )" by (rule MMI_imbi12d)
   have S13: "C = 
 if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 C ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq2)
   have S14: "C = 
 if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⋅ C ) = 
 ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⋅ if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   from S14 have S15: "C = 
 if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⋅ C ) = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟷ 
 ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⋅ if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   from S13 S15 have S16: "C = 
 if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) = C ⟷ ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⋅ C ) = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⟷ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟬 ) ⟷ 
 ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⋅ if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_bibi12d)
   from S16 have S17: "C = 
 if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) = C ⟷ ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⋅ C ) = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ) ⟷ 
 ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟬 ) ⟷ 
 ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⋅ if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ) )" by (rule MMI_imbi2d)
   have S18: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S18 have S19: "if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   have S20: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S20 have S21: "if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   have S22: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S22 have S23: "if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   from S19 S21 S23 have S24: "if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟬 ) ⟷ 
 ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⋅ if ( C ∈ ℂ , C , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_divmulz)
   from S5 S12 S17 S24 have S25: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( B ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = C ⟷ ( B ⋅ C ) = A ) )" by (rule MMI_dedth3h)
   from S25 show "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ∧ B ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = C ⟷ ( B ⋅ C ) = A )" by (rule MMI_imp)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_divmul2t: 
   shows "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ∧ B ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = C ⟷ A = ( B ⋅ C ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ∧ B ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = C ⟷ ( B ⋅ C ) = A )" by (rule MMI_divmult)
   have S2: "( B ⋅ C ) = A ⟷ A = ( B ⋅ C )" by (rule MMI_eqcom)
   from S1 S2 show "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ∧ B ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = C ⟷ A = ( B ⋅ C ) )" by (rule MMI_syl6bb)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_divmul3t: 
   shows "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ∧ B ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = C ⟷ A = ( C ⋅ B ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ∧ B ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = C ⟷ A = ( B ⋅ C ) )" by (rule MMI_divmul2t)
   have S2: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( B ⋅ C ) = ( C ⋅ B )" by (rule MMI_axmulcom)
   from S2 have S3: "( B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A = ( B ⋅ C ) ⟷ A = ( C ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq2d)
   from S3 have S4: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A = ( B ⋅ C ) ⟷ A = ( C ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   from S4 have S5: "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ∧ B ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( A = ( B ⋅ C ) ⟷ A = ( C ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   from S1 S5 show "( ( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ) ∧ B ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) = C ⟷ A = ( C ⋅ B ) )" by (rule MMI_bitrd)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_divcl: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ" and
    A3: "B ≠ 𝟬"   
   shows "( A \<cdiv> B ) ∈ ℂ"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A3 have S3: "B ≠ 𝟬".
   from S1 S2 S3 have S4: "( A \<cdiv> B ) = 
 ⋃ { x ∈ ℂ . ( B ⋅ x ) = A }" by (rule MMI_divval)
   from A2 have S5: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A1 have S6: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A3 have S7: "B ≠ 𝟬".
   from S5 S6 S7 have S8: "∃! x . x ∈ ℂ ∧ ( B ⋅ x ) = A" by (rule MMI_receu)
   have S9: "( ∃! x . x ∈ ℂ ∧ ( B ⋅ x ) = 
 A ) ⟶ ⋃ { x ∈ ℂ . ( B ⋅ x ) = A } ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_reucl)
   from S8 S9 have S10: "⋃ { x ∈ ℂ . ( B ⋅ x ) = A } ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_ax_mp)
   from S4 S10 show "( A \<cdiv> B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_eqeltr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_divclz: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "B ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( A \<cdiv> B ) ∈ ℂ"
proof -
   have S1: "B = 
 if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cdiv> B ) = 
 ( A \<cdiv> if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   from S1 have S2: "B = 
 if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) ∈ ℂ ⟷ 
 ( A \<cdiv> if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) ) ∈ ℂ )" by (rule MMI_eleq1d)
   from A1 have S3: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S4: "B ∈ ℂ".
   have S5: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from S4 S5 have S6: "if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_keepel)
   have S7: "if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_elimne0)
   from S3 S6 S7 have S8: "( A \<cdiv> if ( B ≠ 𝟬 , B , 𝟭 ) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_divcl)
   from S2 S8 show "B ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( A \<cdiv> B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_dedth)
qed

(************** 161-170 *****************************)


lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_divclt: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ B ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cdiv> B ) ∈ ℂ"
proof -
   have S1: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cdiv> B ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> B )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   from S1 have S2: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A \<cdiv> B ) ∈ ℂ ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> B ) ∈ ℂ )" by (rule MMI_eleq1d)
   from S2 have S3: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( B ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( A \<cdiv> B ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟷ 
 ( B ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> B ) ∈ ℂ ) )" by (rule MMI_imbi2d)
   have S4: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( B ≠ 𝟬 ⟷ if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ≠ 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_neeq1)
   have S5: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> B ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   from S5 have S6: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> B ) ∈ ℂ ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) ∈ ℂ )" by (rule MMI_eleq1d)
   from S4 S6 have S7: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( B ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> B ) ∈ ℂ ) ⟷ 
 ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) ∈ ℂ ) )" by (rule MMI_imbi12d)
   have S8: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S8 have S9: "if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   have S10: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S10 have S11: "if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   from S9 S11 have S12: "if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_divclz)
   from S3 S7 S12 have S13: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( B ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( A \<cdiv> B ) ∈ ℂ )" by (rule MMI_dedth2h)
   from S13 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ B ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( A \<cdiv> B ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3impia)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_reccl: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "A ≠ 𝟬"   
   shows "( 𝟭 \<cdiv> A ) ∈ ℂ"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from A1 have S2: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S3: "A ≠ 𝟬".
   from S1 S2 S3 show "( 𝟭 \<cdiv> A ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_divcl)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_recclz: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( 𝟭 \<cdiv> A ) ∈ ℂ"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from A1 have S2: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S1 S2 show "A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( 𝟭 \<cdiv> A ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_divclz)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_recclt: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ ( 𝟭 \<cdiv> A ) ∈ ℂ"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   have S2: "( 𝟭 ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( 𝟭 \<cdiv> A ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_divclt)
   from S1 S2 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ ( 𝟭 \<cdiv> A ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_mp3an1)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_divcan2: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ" and
    A3: "A ≠ 𝟬"   
   shows "( A ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> A ) ) = B"
proof -
   have S1: "( B \<cdiv> A ) = ( B \<cdiv> A )" by (rule MMI_eqid)
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A1 have S3: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S4: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A1 have S5: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A3 have S6: "A ≠ 𝟬".
   from S4 S5 S6 have S7: "( B \<cdiv> A ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_divcl)
   from A3 have S8: "A ≠ 𝟬".
   from S2 S3 S7 S8 have S9: "( B \<cdiv> A ) = 
 ( B \<cdiv> A ) ⟷ ( A ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> A ) ) = B" by (rule MMI_divmul)
   from S1 S9 show "( A ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> A ) ) = B" by (rule MMI_mpbi)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_divcan1: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ" and
    A3: "A ≠ 𝟬"   
   shows "( ( B \<cdiv> A ) ⋅ A ) = B"
proof -
   from A2 have S1: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A1 have S2: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A3 have S3: "A ≠ 𝟬".
   from S1 S2 S3 have S4: "( B \<cdiv> A ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_divcl)
   from A1 have S5: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S4 S5 have S6: "( ( B \<cdiv> A ) ⋅ A ) = ( A ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> A ) )" by (rule MMI_mulcom)
   from A1 have S7: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from A2 have S8: "B ∈ ℂ".
   from A3 have S9: "A ≠ 𝟬".
   from S7 S8 S9 have S10: "( A ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> A ) ) = B" by (rule MMI_divcan2)
   from S6 S10 show "( ( B \<cdiv> A ) ⋅ A ) = B" by (rule MMI_eqtr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_divcan1z: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( ( B \<cdiv> A ) ⋅ A ) = B"
proof -
   have S1: "A = 
 if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( B \<cdiv> A ) = 
 ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   have S2: "A = 
 if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 A = if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 )" by (rule MMI_id)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "A = 
 if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( B \<cdiv> A ) ⋅ A ) = 
 ( ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ) ⋅ if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq12d)
   from S3 have S4: "A = 
 if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( B \<cdiv> A ) ⋅ A ) = 
 B ⟷ 
 ( ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ) ⋅ if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ) = 
 B )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   from A1 have S5: "A ∈ ℂ".
   have S6: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from S5 S6 have S7: "if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_keepel)
   from A2 have S8: "B ∈ ℂ".
   have S9: "if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_elimne0)
   from S7 S8 S9 have S10: "( ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ) ⋅ if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ) = 
 B" by (rule MMI_divcan1)
   from S4 S10 show "A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( ( B \<cdiv> A ) ⋅ A ) = B" by (rule MMI_dedth)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_divcan2z: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( A ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> A ) ) = B"
proof -
   have S1: "A = 
 if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 A = if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 )" by (rule MMI_id)
   have S2: "A = 
 if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( B \<cdiv> A ) = 
 ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "A = 
 if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> A ) ) = 
 ( if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq12d)
   from S3 have S4: "A = 
 if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> A ) ) = 
 B ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ) ) = 
 B )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   from A1 have S5: "A ∈ ℂ".
   have S6: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from S5 S6 have S7: "if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_keepel)
   from A2 have S8: "B ∈ ℂ".
   have S9: "if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_elimne0)
   from S7 S8 S9 have S10: "( if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ≠ 𝟬 , A , 𝟭 ) ) ) = 
 B" by (rule MMI_divcan2)
   from S4 S10 show "A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( A ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> A ) ) = B" by (rule MMI_dedth)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_divcan1t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( B \<cdiv> A ) ⋅ A ) = B"
proof -
   have S1: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( A ≠ 𝟬 ⟷ if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ≠ 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_neeq1)
   have S2: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( B \<cdiv> A ) = 
 ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   have S3: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_id)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( B \<cdiv> A ) ⋅ A ) = 
 ( ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq12d)
   from S4 have S5: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( B \<cdiv> A ) ⋅ A ) = 
 B ⟷ 
 ( ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 B )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   from S1 S5 have S6: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( ( B \<cdiv> A ) ⋅ A ) = B ) ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
 ( ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 B ) )" by (rule MMI_imbi12d)
   have S7: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   from S7 have S8: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 ( ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq1d)
   have S9: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 B = if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_id)
   from S8 S9 have S10: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 B ⟷ 
 ( ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq12d)
   from S10 have S11: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) = B ) ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
 ( ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_imbi2d)
   have S12: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S12 have S13: "if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   have S14: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S14 have S15: "if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   from S13 S15 have S16: "if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
 ( ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ⋅ if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_divcan1z)
   from S6 S11 S16 have S17: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( ( B \<cdiv> A ) ⋅ A ) = B )" by (rule MMI_dedth2h)
   from S17 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( B \<cdiv> A ) ⋅ A ) = B" by (rule MMI_3impia)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_divcan2t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> A ) ) = B"
proof -
   have S1: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( A ≠ 𝟬 ⟷ if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ≠ 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_neeq1)
   have S2: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 A = if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_id)
   have S3: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( B \<cdiv> A ) = 
 ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> A ) ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq12d)
   from S4 have S5: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> A ) ) = 
 B ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ) = 
 B )" by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   from S1 S5 have S6: "A = 
 if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( A ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> A ) ) = B ) ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ) = 
 B ) )" by (rule MMI_imbi12d)
   have S7: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) = 
 ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   from S7 have S8: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ) = 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_opreq2d)
   have S9: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 B = if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_id)
   from S8 S9 have S10: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ) = 
 B ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ) = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) )" by (rule MMI_eqeq12d)
   from S10 have S11: "B = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ) = B ) ⟷ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ) = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ) )" by (rule MMI_imbi2d)
   have S12: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S12 have S13: "if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   have S14: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S14 have S15: "if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   from S13 S15 have S16: "if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
 ( if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ⋅ ( if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 ) \<cdiv> if ( A ∈ ℂ , A , 𝟬 ) ) ) = 
 if ( B ∈ ℂ , B , 𝟬 )" by (rule MMI_divcan2z)
   from S6 S11 S16 have S17: "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ) ⟶ 
 ( A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ ( A ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> A ) ) = B )" by (rule MMI_dedth2h)
   from S17 show "( A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ) ⟶ 
 ( A ⋅ ( B \<cdiv> A ) ) = B" by (rule MMI_3impia)
qed
